title: quick 'n easy rice pudding
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with brown sugar.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cook a potato and save water.
Put through a sieve and save 1/3 cup mashed potatoes; add potato water to make 3/4 cup.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise. Wash in vinegar and water. Boil eggplant until tender.
Drain water.
Cook onion, tomatoes, garlic and cooking oil on low heat until tender.
Remove the pulp of the eggplant and add to the cooking vegetables.
Add meat and seasonings.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Fill eggplant shells with mixture.
Spread catsup on top of filled shells with a spoon.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: sylvia's punch
directions: Combine strawberries, sugar and 1/2 gallon wine. Let stand for 1 hour. Strain out the strawberries and add rest of ingredients. Put in punch bowl with block of ice.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter over medium heat and add flour to make a paste.
Add milk and bring to a slow boil.
Stir until mixture is thick.
Add cheese.
Mix with macaroni.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Put tomato halves, cut side up, in a shallow baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Mix olive oil, garlic, salt, pepper and marjoram.
Spoon an equal amount onto the tomato halves. Sprinkle with parsley and cheese. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Cook pizza crust at 325° to 350° until golden brown. Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until smooth. Spread over cooled crust. Sprinkle dill weed and add other ingredients.

title: caramel apple cereal squares
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cereal, apples and peanuts.
Mix well.
In a small saucepan, over low heat, combine caramels and milk, stirring frequently, until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour caramel mixture over cereal mixture, toss to coat.
Press into greased pan.
Let stand 1 hour or until firm.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point.
Stir in Jell-O to dissolve. Let cool to room temperature.
Add Cool Whip and buttermilk.
Stir until smooth.
Add pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole, sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: shrimp creole 2
directions: In microwave, simmer celery and onion in milk and Butter Buds. Add shrimp and cheese and microwave until cheese melts; thicken with cornstarch.
Serve over brown rice.
(Add no salt; celery has all that is needed for flavor).
Contains 200 calories per 1/2 cup shrimp sauce.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir spinach, sour cream, mayo, soup mix, and onions until well mixed.
Cover; chill for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Separately mix flour, salt and baking soda, then mix butter or margarine with peanut butter and eggs; beat well.
Add flour and peanut butter mixtures together.
Bake on greased cookie sheet, one teaspoon flattened cookie dough at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 48 to 60 cookies.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to scalding.
Pour over coarse bread crumbs.
Cool and add:
butter, sugar, eggs, salt, raisins, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into a 1 1/2 quart buttered casserole pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a large bowl.
Spoon into crust and dot with
margarine.
Bake at 375° for 37 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Pat firmly on bottom of 9-inch springform pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk; beat until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In mixing bowl, stir together both corns, sour cream, egg, Jiffy mix and butter. Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 40 to 60 minutes or until the top is a medium to dark brown.

title: smoked dove and quail breast
directions: Marinate dove and
quail
breast by seasoning them with salt, pepper and fajita seasoning to your liking.
Pour enough Worcestershire sauce to
saturate all the dove or quail breast you will be
cooking.
Put
in
the
refrigerator
to marinate overnight or at least all day long.

title: easy italian casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook and stir beef, onion and garlic until brown, then drain.
Stir in sauce, mushrooms, sugar, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix baking mix, milk and egg.
Spread half in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan; top with 4 cheese slices.
Spoon beef over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese slices.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Drop remaining dough by spoonfuls onto cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat
cream
cheese,
powdered sugar and whipping cream all together.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Refrigerate 2 hours
before
serving
so	it will be firm to slice. (Pie crust needs to be deep dish large crust.)

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
In same pan put oil, butter, salt and red pepper.
Simmer.
Beat eggs well.
Cook pasta in 5 quarts salted boiling water.
Cook al dente on hard side.
Drain pasta. Put in bowl.
Pour egg over pasta, then oil and butter mixture, then cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry banana split
directions: Mix melted oleo and graham crackers.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate.
Mix and beat on medium speed for 15 minutes the eggs, powdered sugar and 2 sticks of oleo.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture on crumbs.
Layer bananas, pineapple and strawberries (frozen or fresh), all diced small.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: party mix
directions: Combine chocolate, peanut butter and margarine; melt over low heat.
Add Rice Chex; fold gently until all are coated.
Add sugar and fold until all are coated.

title: bow ties (a finger food)
directions: Remove crusts from bread as you like.
Spread with cream of mushroom soup.
Roll corners opposite and secure with 1/2 strip of bacon, overlapping it.
Bake in a slow 300° oven for 1 hour.
You can spread bread with margarine, if desired.
It is best if they set overnight before baking.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and serve ice cold.

title: tortellini bites
directions: Reserve 1 1/4 cups broth.
Bring remaining broth to a boil in large pot.
Add tortellini and cook until tender.
Drain.
In a small bowl, blend cornstarch into 1 1/4 cup of reserved broth.
In a large saucepan, saute garlic and basil in margarine for 2 minutes over medium heat.
Add cornstarch-broth mixture to the saucepan.
Cook and stir until the mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Place tortellini in a serving dish and pour the broth- mixture and the Parmesan cheese into the serving dish and toss. Serve with toothpicks.

title: strawberry-banana float
directions: In mixing bowl of blender, blend ice cream with strawberries and bananas.
Gradually add milk and orange juice.
Pour into large glasses.
Top with scoops of ice cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs; stir in dry ingredients. Chill.
Roll into walnut sized balls.
Roll balls in mixture of 1 teaspoon of sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Bake 400 degrees for 8-10 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until cake springs back to touch.

title: cherry jubilee pie
directions: Beat together softened cream cheese, sugar, eggs and milk until creamy.
Pour into pie crust and bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour cherry pie filling on top. Cool and serve.

title: blue cheese coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the cabbage and Blue cheese and chill the mixture, covered, for 1 hour.
While the cabbage mixture is chilling, in a bowl, whisk together the vinegar, mustard, celery seeds, garlic, salt, white pepper, sugar and onion. Add the oil in a stream, whisking.
Whisk until emulsified. Chill dressing, covered, for 1 hour.
Pour over the cabbage mixture and toss coleslaw until combined well.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Sift flour and baking powder.
In medium pan bring to a boil blueberries, fructose, 1/4 cup honey, lemon and water.
Cream butter and 1/3 cup honey.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Pour hot blueberries in 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Spoon flour mixture over the top. Bake 25 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Serves 12.

title: scripture cake
directions: Sift together 1 Kings, 2 Chronicles, Leviticus and Amos.
Add to first mixture.
Lastly, add Judges.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: quick peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar in iron skillet over medium heat, stirring often. Sprinkle soda over peanuts.
When sugar has completely melted, quickly pour peanuts and soda into sugar; stir and pour immediately onto greased cookie sheet.
(The soda will cause the sugar to foam and make the candy airy and light).
Let cool. Break up candy by dropping pan onto countertop after it is completely cool.

title: new zealand pavlova cake(in honor of stallions, "bill b." and "great evander")
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until quite stiff; fold in sugar. Add vanilla and vinegar.
Place on greased paper or aluminum foil on a tray (cookie sheet) and bake very slowly for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 250°.
When baked, pile sweetened whipped cream on top and drained fruit cocktail on top.
Use a large can of fruit cocktail (be sure it is drained extremely well.
Cut the Pavlova into squares and serve on small dessert plates.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg. Combine remaining 3/4 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, egg and melted margarine in bowl until crumbly.
Spread over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
May substitute apples for fresh peaches.
Bake apple crisp at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: mom's green beans
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until hot.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Drain. Salt and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1/4 cup milk together in pan.
Add remaining milk.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add enough liquid to make a smooth paste.
Add the paste mixture to the milk and also add the chocolate pieces.
Cook over a medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from
heat and add vanilla. Pour into crust.

title: sunshine muffins
directions: Cut up orange into 8 pieces.
Put in blender; add orange juice, egg and oil.
Blend until smooth.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour blender mixture over dry ingredients; stir until just mixed.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
12 large.

title: shut-up dawgs(hush puppies)
directions: Preheat oil to 360°.
Mix all the dry ingredients together. Add egg and milk; mix thoroughly.
Drop batter by teaspoon into deep hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook meat the night before.
Cook water, celery and parsley together for 20 minutes.
Strain it and save the juice.
Saute 1 large onion (cut small) in margarine.
Add in remaining ingredients plus shredded beef.
Cook until warmed through, about 45 minutes over medium heat, stirring frequently.

title: cajun meat loaf
directions: Melt butter over medium heat or spray pan with cooking spray. Add onions, celery, peppers, & green onions, garlic, tabasco, worcestershire and "seasoning mix". Saute until mixture starts excessively sticking to pan, about 6 minutes. Stir in milk and catsup. Continue cooking 2 minutes, stirring. Remove from heat and allow to cool to room temperature. Place meat in bowl. Add eggs, vegetable mixture (REMOVE THE BAY LEAVES AT THIS TIME!) and the bread crumbs. Thoroughly mix by hand. Pack meatloaf into an ungreased bread pan. Bake at 350 degrees uncovered for 25 minutes, then 400 degrees for 35 minutes. Serve plain or top with catsup before baking.

title: anniversary cake
directions: In bowl, prepare 2 cake mixes according to package directions, but increasing mixing time by one-half.
Fill paper lined 10 x 2 and 6 x 2-inch round pans half full.
Prepare remaining cake mix and pour into 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven until done, about 45 minutes for 6-inch, 50 minutes for 8-inch layer and 55 minutes for 10-inch layer.
Cool.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Cook
cauliflower
in
small amount of water.
Place in casserole.	Sprinkle cheese and salt on top.
Put bread crumbs on top
of that.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: stir-fried shrimp chow mein
directions: Heat frying pan with enough oil just to coat the surface.
Add thinly sliced onion and green pepper.
Cook only until onion is translucent.
Do not overcook.
Remove onion and green pepper from frying pan and drain on paper towel.
Some oil will remain in the skillet.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips in microwave until melted.
Stir cereal into mix.
Coat all cereal with mixture.
Put coated cereal into a container where you can shake it up in the powdered sugar to coat it thoroughly.
(You sometimes need to use more sugar.)
All should be covered until white.
Pour onto waxed paper until set and dry.

title: annette's fried pies
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Pour Wesson oil and milk into one measuring cup.
Don't stir.
Add all at once to the flour.
Stir until mixed.
Shape into balls.
Place balls between two 12-inch squares of waxed paper.
(Dampen table top to keep from slipping.) Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Peel off top paper.
Cut into 5-inch squares or circles.
Place a large spoonful of filling on each circle. Fold over filling to make a half circle.
Seal edges with a fork dipped in flour.
Fry 4 or 5 minutes in 1-inch of oil.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake at 325°.
Cool to cut.

title: light tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water (without added salt) until al dente and drain.

Melt margarine in saucepan over moderate heat and blend in flour; slowly add milk and stir until slightly thickened. Remove from heat; combine noodles with sauce, then mix in drained tuna and remaining ingredients except topping.
Spoon into 2 quart casserole sprayed with vegetable oil cooking spray and sprinkle bread crumbs over surface.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4; contains 440 calories and 7 grams fat.

title: rocky mountain sweeties
directions: Melt the white chocolate and 2 cups of peanut butter over boiling water or microwave about 5 minutes until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper. Refrigerate to harden.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and place into greased casserole dish.
Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter.
Add cheese, soups, seasoning, cayenne pepper and broccoli.
Pour sauce over rice.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil 3 minutes. Add tomato paste.
Saute a few minutes more.
Add tomatoes which have been quickly crushed in blender. Add all spices.
Reduce to low heat.
Cook 2 hours, covered.

title: crustless potato quiche
directions: Combine eggs, hash browns, cheese, onion, cottage cheese, salt, pepper and dash of hot sauce; stir well.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle bacon evenly on top.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yield:
one 9-inch quiche.

title: chocolate peanut butter chip glazed fudge
directions: Line 8 or 9 inch square pan with wax paper.

title: brownie cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in an oblong pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions and celery in 5 cups water until tender; add cream of chicken soup and 1/2 can of milk.
Add other ingredients and simmer.
Add cheese last and continue to heat until cheese is melted.
Be sure to stir often for cheese will stick to kettle.

title: mrs. johnson's oriental salad
directions: In a large bowl, put the first 8 ingredients all drained. Heat the sugar and vinegar.
Pour the heated mixture over the vegetables. Toss several times until coated.
Chill before serving.
Will keep a week in refrigerator.

title: mary's kanaka stew
directions: Brown stew meat with a sprinkle of Hawaiian or rock salt.
Add onion and cook until onion is translucent.
Add in carrots, potatoes and tomato sauce.
Put enough water to cover.
Add the bay leaves.
Bring to a boil, then let simmer for about an hour or until meat is tender.
Adjust seasoning with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Serve with poi.
Sprinkle lightly salted chopped lipoa (seaweed) on top of your bowl of stew for a real Hawaiian treat.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Cut steak into squares.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with 2 cans of soup.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour at 400°.
Serve over rice.

title: layered spinach supreme
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches.
Mix baking mix, milk, eggs and the onion; beat vigorously.
Spread in dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon evenly over batter in dish.
Bake until set, about 30 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form into a ball, then roll in parsley flakes.
Should be kept in refrigerator at least overnight before using.

title: great fried potatoes
directions: Peel desired amount of potatoes.
Slice as you like.
Heat bacon grease in frying pan.
Add potatoes and onion sprinkled with garlic salt, salt, red pepper and black pepper.
Stir as needed. Cook until golden brown on outside and tender on the inside. Drain grease.
Serve warm.

title: hot buttered rum batter
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, nutmeg and cinnamon with electric mixer.
Blend in softened ice cream.
Turn into a 4-cup freezer container.
Seal and freeze (will not freeze solid).

title: oven parmesan chips
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut washed, unpeeled potatoes into 1/8-inch thick slices and place in single layer on lightly buttered baking sheet.
Melt butter (margarine) in small saucepan and add onion, salt and pepper to taste and paprika.
Brush mixture on potatoes and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are crisp and golden.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve at once.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked apricots
directions: Drain and cut apricots into fourths.
In a greased 2-quart casserole dish, put a layer of apricots.
Cover with brown sugar, then a layer of the crumbled crackers and dot thickly with lumps of margarine.
Repeat layers.
Bake slowly in a 300° oven for approximately 1 hour.
It should be thick and crusty on top. Serves 10.

title: french bread dip
directions: Saute garlic and onions in oleo.
Mix well with cream cheese, sour cream and cheese.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper. Dig out French bread and cut into cubes.
Fill shell with dip. Wrap in foil and bake for 2 hours at 275°.
Serve with reserved bread cubes or chips.

title: 1, 2, 3 cake(quick and easy)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake according to cake mix package instructions.
Needs no frosting.
Just sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs, one at a time, then add flour.
Add 1 tablespoon of milk if needed.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven door.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan melt 6 tablespoons margarine.
Stir in oats, sugar, flour and baking soda.
Press firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place hash browns on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream and pepper.
Place on top of hash browns.
Then mix 1/2 can French fried onions and 1/2 of cheese on top of first mixture.
Place browned pork chops on top.
Bake covered at 350° for 40 minutes, then place rest of cheese and onions on top.
Bake uncovered for 10 more minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dingbats
directions: Combine margarine and sugar.
Add well beaten egg and chopped dates.
Cook over low heat until dissolved.
Add 1 cup pecans and cook 10 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla; stir.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well. Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: kringla
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Beat the eggs well, then add. Mix the flour, baking soda and baking powder together, then alternate with the buttermilk, a little at a time.
Mix in the vanilla and salt.
Refrigerate overnight.
Make short ropes and twist as pretzels.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until set, does not brown.

title: corn light bread
directions: Thicken again with meal and let stand overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Stir in dry ingredients, then add bananas and nuts.
Place in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° at least 1 hour until crack in top of loaf looks dry. Turn out onto rack to cool.

title: tuna mold
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water; set aside.
Combine tomato soup and cream cheese in medium saucepan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring until well blended.
Stir in softened gelatin until dissolved.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients to cooled cheese mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill several hours. Serve with crackers.

title: rice pudding
directions: Separate eggs and beat the yolks.
Add sugar, salt, milk, vanilla and rice.
Stiffly beat the egg whites and fold into mixture.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread, and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Cut top off bread; run hand along inside crust and pull out soft bread.
Fill crust with dip.
Cube bread and top crust.
The shell serves as bowl and arrange cubed bread around it.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350°.

title: dee's heath bar cake
directions: Mix and bake cake per directions on package in an oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven and punch holes with knife blade when slightly cooled.
Pour sweetened condensed milk and butterscotch sauce over the cake.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or as needed.

title: fruit salad
directions: Any fresh fruit can be used.

title: chicken francaise
directions: Heat oil in a skillet on high.
Salt and dredge chicken cutlets in flour and then dip into egg mixture and place in skillet.
Fry quickly and turn.
(They will be very light brown.)
Clean skillet and melt butter; add chopped garlic and lower heat to medium, stirring constantly.
(Do not brown garlic.)
Add lemon juice and stir in white wine.
Heat for a few more minutes.
Place chicken in a pan and pour mixture over it.
Place in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix together 2 1/4 cups flour with sugar; cut in butter as for pastry.
Bind together with egg yolk.
Knead lightly using other 1/4 cup flour as needed.
Divide into 4 portions.
Roll each one out to a 1/2-inch circle.
Score edges and prick center with fork. Mark into wedges with knife going down 1/8-inch.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes; let cool 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: mother's potato cake(old, old recipe)
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix together and drop by large spoon into skillet and fry in oil in patties.

title: cabbage souffle salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Blend in mayonnaise.
Add cold water, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Beat until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into 1-quart mold. Chill until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put syrup, sugar and peanuts in iron frying pan.
Cook on low heat.
When it begins to boil, increase the heat to 300°.
Take off burner and add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon soda and beat. Turn out on buttered cookie sheet.

title: hello dollies
directions: Place in pan in order given and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except 7-Up.
Freeze; take out approximately 2 hours before serving.
Add 7-Up and serve.
Makes 75 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add orange juice. Chill until slightly thickened.
Add oranges, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Pour half jello mixture into a 1 1/2-quart mold or pan and chill until firm.
Combine cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread over jello mixture. Pour remaining jello mixture over the cheese layer.
Chill.

title: cheddar stack cakes
directions: In a medium saucepan combine 2 cups water, dried fruit, brown sugar, lemon juice and nutmeg; heat to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Stir in peaches; keep warm.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla.
Add bananas. Sift together flour and soda.
Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pans (two), Bundt pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn and broccoli bake
directions: Thaw corn and broccoli in the microwave.
Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend in flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in milk and eggs; blend well.
Add corn and stir.
Cover.
Microwave on Power level 7 for 12 to 15 minutes.
When done, center will be barely set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Grate all cheeses and mix together.
Add other ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Form into ball and chill.

title: sandies
directions: Mix together.
Shape into crescents.
Place on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: crock-pot chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and onion in 2 quarts water in crock-pot until done.
Take chicken out and debone, reserving the broth in crock-pot.
Cook 15 or 20 minutes (until done).
Stir in the chicken, vegetables, cream of chicken soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Good with cranberry sauce.

title: butter-herbed baked fish
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan
Combine cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, salt and garlic powder.
Dip fish in fillets in butter, then into crumb mixture.
Arrange in baking pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini pie(apple)
directions: Mix sugar, salt and spice with the zucchini.
Add lemon juice and cook until zucchini is soft.
Add cornstarch mixture and cool for a few minutes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown. Tastes like an apple pie.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine crumbs, peanut butter, butter and sugar.
Work together until smooth.
Press mixture into a 9 x 9-inch pan (or longer if you want thinner bars).
Melt chocolate chips over hot water, spread over cracker mixture.
Refrigerate until cool, cut in squares.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Oil and flour 2 round cake pans. Beat egg whites until fluffy. Beat in 1/2 cup sugar until stiff.
Set aside.
Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder and salt. Add oil, 1/2 cup milk and vanilla. Beat at medium speed. Add remaining milk and egg yolks. Beat 1 minute. Fold in chocolate, egg whites and sugar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hello dollies!
directions: Combine melted margarine and cracker crumbs.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given. Drizzle sweetened condensed milk over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cut while still warm.

title: seasoned pork chops
directions: In a large skillet on low heat cook
pork chops slowly. When brown on one side, turn over and
sprinkle	on
seasoned salt. Continue to cook slowly and turn
often; season lightly each time you turn.
Cook thoroughly, but do	not
burn, about 30 minutes.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Mix together potatoes, 1 cup cheese, soups, onion, sour cream and melted butter in a large bowl.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until mixture is bubbly.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and paprika and bake 10 minutes more. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cover chops.
Simmer until tender or bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: grandma's tortchen cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter.
Add sugar; cream.
Add eggs; cream.
Add flour mixed with salt.
Make little balls; flatten.
Make a hole in the center.
Brush with egg white; fill with marmalade (we use raspberry preserves).

title: cornbread (mexican)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour half of batter in greased pan.
Sprinkle cheese over the batter.
Pour rest of batter over cheese.
Cook at 375° for one hour or until golden brown.

title: butter pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into graham cracker crust and let set for 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: green peas and potatoes
directions: Cook peas and celery following directions.
Mix soup and water; stir and bring to a boil.
Add potatoes.
Whip with fork until smooth.
Spoon onto a platter.
Hollow center of potatoes to make a nest.
Spoon peas into hollow.

title: pecan dandie balls
directions: Cream together butter, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add pecans and flour; mix until becomes a dough.
Roll the dough by tablespoons into small balls; place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
While still warm from oven, roll balls in confectioners sugar.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until creamy. Stir in sifted dry ingredients. Add vanilla, nuts and apple. Mix well. Pour into a 10-inch greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cut into wedges and serve warm with ice cream.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Simmer chicken in 2 quarts of water, seasoned with salt and pepper, covered, for 3 hours or until fork-tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Bring broth to a boil; add spaghetti and cook for about 8 minutes.
Drain and reserve broth.
Remove skin and bones from chicken and separate into small pieces.
Add back to broth. Boil down to 2 cups; strain.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Stir in zucchini.
Continue the rest of ingredients in a separate bowl.
Combine with zucchini mixture.
Mix well. Pour into two greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Delicious!!!

title: spring wop balls
directions: Mix all together, drop by teaspoons in hot oil.
Brown both sides and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or granulated sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Butter a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine all but croutons and cheese.
Top with croutons and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all well and store in airtight container.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup.
Great for camping!!

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Heat sugar and Karo until it barely boils.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Add cornflakes.
Stir to coat.
Pour into greased pan.
Cut when cool.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies to dirt consistency in food processor.
Cream the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding and milk.
When thick, beat in cream mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip. Layer in a 9-inch flowerpot dirt and cream mixture.
Start and end with dirt.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In large bowl, stir 1 c. sugar, 2 sticks melted margarine, 1 1/2 tsp. salt, and 1 c. boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
In a small bowl, dissolve 2 pkg. dry yeast into 1 c. warm tap water. Beat 2 eggs and add to yeast mixture.
Combine yeast and eggs with first mixture.
Stir in 2 lb. (6 c.) flour.
Keep in bowl and put on lid.
Refrigerate at least four hours before using.
Shape the rolls, dip them in flour, and then in melted margarine.
Place in greased pan.
Let set out 3 hours before baking and do not cover. Bake in 400 degree oven about 12 minutes.

title: simple fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine	in
a
shallow	baking dish.
Pour well mixed flour,
sugar and milk mixture into melted margarine. Do not stir. Then
add	fruit.	Bake
at
350°	for
45 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over crust; return to oven 10 minutes.
The crust will rise to top and your fruit will spread throughout mixture as well. Serve topped with ice cream.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Chop the pecans and coconut and sprinkle in a 13 x 15-inch sheet cake pan.
Follow the directions on the box of cake mix and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Drizzle over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana brunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine pancake mix, 3/4 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add bananas, milk, egg and oil; mix well.
Spread into prepared pan.
Combine nuts, 1/4 cup brown sugar and margarine.
Sprinkle evenly over batter. Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cinnamon pull-apart
directions: Defrost bread.
Stretch and make 20 balls per loaf.
Mix cinnamon, sugar and flour.
Melt butter, drizzle 1 to 2 tablespoons in Bundt pan.
Turn dough balls in butter and roll in cinnamon mixture, place in pan.
Make 2 layers.
Sprinkle cinnamon mixture in bottom of pan, sprinkle with pecans (optional).
Also repeat in between layers.
Using extra butter and cinnamon mixture, pour over bread.
Rise until double size.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: garden vegetable burrito
directions: In large skillet add butter, zucchini, mushrooms, broccoli, bell pepper and jalapeno.
Saute on medium heat for 5 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Reduce heat; add corn and cumin. Heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and quickly blend in cheese.
Serve with mango.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Mix brown sugar and cornstarch in deep skillet.
Stir in pineapple chunks with syrup, vinegar and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; reduce heat.
Add cooked chicken; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in green pepper; simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate-covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries thoroughly on paper toweling.
Combine butter or margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Knead mixture until smooth (chill mixture if too soft).
Shape 1 teaspoon of the sugar mixture around each cherry.
Place coated cherries on a baking sheet lined with waxed paper; chill.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put all ingredients in a large baking dish.
Put chicken on top.
Cut one stick oleo on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Remove foil and bake about 15 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix as directed on box.
Bake in 2 layers.
When cool, split each layer to make 4 layers.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Heat approximately 1/2 cup olive oil in a large heavy skillet over low to medium heat.
In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix.
Add water, about 2 tablespoons at a time, while stirring until mixture is sticky.
Scrape out on floured surface.
Knead in small amount of flour until slightly stiff.

title: ham casserole
directions: In a greased dish, layer noodles, ham and Parmesan cheese. Repeat in same order.

title: viola's baked fish
directions: Quarter potatoes and onions.
Cook for 30 minutes in pot of water.
Roll fish in butter, salt and pepper.
Place skin down in baking pan.
Put bacon on fish.
With slotted spoon, put potatoes and onion on and around fish.
Pour canned tomatoes on top.
Then add bell pepper.
Pour some of juice from potatoes and onion on fish until almost covered.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown meat in oil lightly.
Add onion, garlic, celery and carrots.
Continue cooking until all browned.
Add soup, cheese and seasonings.
Thin with milk if necessary.
Line dish with pie crust.
Pour mixture into crust.
Top with second crust.
Cut 3 to 4 slits in crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until crust is desired shade of brown.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in pan. Boil 1 minute; keep stirring. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips; keep stirring. Will thicken as it cools. Best to put warm on warm cake.

title: vermont spinach salad
directions: Wash, dry and stem spinach and place in a serving bowl.
Cut apple in half; cut each half into 1/2-inch chunks and add to spinach.
Chop egg and crumble bacon and add to spinach.
Toss until evenly distributed.
Add cheese and toss.
In a small saucepan, whisk together maple syrup and 1/3 cup vinegar.
Taste and add 1 to 2 more tablespoons vinegar, if desired.
Add salt and pepper.
Heat until warm.
Pour warm dressing over spinach; toss and serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Bake in 15 x 11-inch pan.
While warm, poke holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk over all.
Pour 1/2 jar of caramel ice cream topping over cake and Eagle Brand.
Cool in refrigerator.
Spread with large Cool Whip.
Crumble Butterfinger candy bar over top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: scallopini of venison
directions: Wipe meat with vinegar-soaked cloth.
(Vinegar will pick up hairs.)
Cut meat into serving pieces and roll lightly in seasoned flour.
Flatten slightly with edge of plate or meat pounder.
Fry until golden brown on both sides in hot fat.
Add onions after first turning.
Place in greased casserole; add remaining ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 2 hours, until tender.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
(Can add carrots and potatoes.)

title: sugared cranberry trail mix
directions: Spread almonds evenly on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 7 or 8 minutes or until nuts are slightly darker in color.
Cool completely on pan.

title: ham casserole
directions: Heat cheese, milk and Miracle Whip over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in large iron skillet at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar together with fork.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and baking powder.
Then add flour and milk.
Mix together with spoon or fork until stiff dough forms.
Drop by rounded balls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until lightly brown or done to taste.
Also, chocolate chips, nuts, or other ingredients may be added for extra taste.

title: fried okra
directions: Fry sausage or bacon separately.
Melt oleo to cover skillet bottom.
Fry okra in oleo on medium heat without cover.
Cut up tomatoes and onion into skillet with okra.
Let okra cook until slightly browned or done looking.
Put in bacon bits and/or sausage; season to taste.

title: brownies(1944 recipe)
directions: Mix eggs, which have been beaten, with sugar; beat well.
Melt butter and stir in cocoa.
Add to egg mixture.
Add flour and vanilla.
Fold in nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 300° in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
When pan has cooled, cut in squares.
Double recipe and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: killed lettuce
directions: Clean lettuce.
Add onions.
Mix together vinegar, salt and brown sugar.
Pour over lettuce.
Heat grease and pour over lettuce.
Eat immediately.

title: grandma mag's jello cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients into shortening until mixed well.
Add eggs and extract, mix.
Refrigerate for about an hour for easier handling.
Then roll out on floured surface.
Cut as desired. Bake in 350° oven until set or light brown, about 10 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a skillet, add oil.
Put flour, salt and pepper in a baggie.
Add meat a little at a time.
Shake to coat.
Add to hot oil and brown.
Scrape all into crock-pot.
Add enough beef broth to cover.
Heat on high for 1 hour.
Turn to low; let cook 6 to 8 hours (until meat is tender).
Fifteen minutes before serving, add mushrooms.
Cook either rice or noodles.
Just before serving, add sour cream.

title: taco casserole
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco seasoning according to packet and simmer.
Crush chips and sprinkle over bottom of a 9x9 pan.
Top with hamburger mixture then spread cheese soup over all.
Sprinkle with tomato and mozzarella cheese. Bake uncovered for 20 minutes, or until cheese is golden brown on top.
Top with lettuce and sour cream, then serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini, carrots and onion in oleo (approximately 5 minutes).
Add sour cream, soup and 1 can of water.
Mix stuffing mix as directed on package.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup dry stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers in oleo.
Add ground round and scramble fry.
Add garlic or use garlic powder.
Add dry taco mix, dry Ranch dressing, Tabasco sauce and lemon pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Let set for 4 hours.
May serve soup over corn chips and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: scampi for two
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat. Stir in garlic (do not brown). Add shrimp and saute 1 to 2 minutes (until opaque). Take up shrimp. Bring sauce to boil quickly until thick.
Pour over shrimp.

title: lye soap
directions: Pour 2 1/2 pints of water in granite pan or any container not aluminum.
Pour lye in water and stir well until dissolved.
Let stand for 1/2 day; melt grease and strain.
Stir in lye mixture and stir until thick and looks white.
Let set overnight.
Cut out.

title: cantaloupe soup
directions: Cut cantaloupe in half and remove seeds.
Peel each and cut fruit into 1-inch cubes.
Combine half of cantaloupes and 1/2 cup orange juice in container of an electric blender; process until mixture is smooth.
Repeat processing with remaining cantaloupe cubes and an additional 1/2 cup orange juice.
Combine cantaloupe mixture, remaining 3 1/2 cups orange juice and next 3 ingredients, blending well; cover and chill thoroughly.
Garnish with mint leaves, if desired.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: In a bowl mix sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add beaten eggs and fruit cocktail, stir well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: good for you pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle pan with cornmeal.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface to a 16 x 11-inch rectangle.
Transfer dough to prepared pan.
Build up edges slightly.
Do not let rise.
Bake for about 12 minutes, or until brown.
Spread sauce over crust.
Layer with seasonings, vegetables and cheeses.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes more, or until bubbly.
Serve while hot.

title: miss daisy's tea punch
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water.
Remove bags; discard. Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Put tea water in gallon pitcher. Add concentrates and water to make a gallon.
Stir before each use.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: baked spinach parmesan dip
directions: Squeeze spinach to remove liquid. With a mixer, beat spinach, mayonnaise, cream cheese, onion, garlic, 1 cup parmesan and pepper until thoroughly combined.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in shallow 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Top each piece with a slice of Swiss cheese.
In a small bowl, stir together soup and water, spoon evenly over chicken. Sprinkle stuffing mix over chicken.
Drizzle evenly with melted butter.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is cooked and no longer pink.

title: zucchini and tomato saute
directions: Saute onion in oil in a frypan until soft.
Mix in garlic, tomatoes, salt, basil, sugar, oregano, pepper and chicken broth. Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer 20 minutes, covered.
At the end of 20 minutes, uncover.
Mix in zucchini; over medium heat, cook until tomato sauce is reduced and thickened, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Salt to taste and serve.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat together egg yolks, Eagle Brand and lime juice.
Pour into pie crust and bake 30 minutes.
Cool. Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
When mixing ingredients, you can add green coloring, if desired.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine sour cream, chicken soup, pimento and onion with mashed squash.
Melt margarine and mix with herb seasoning or cornbread stuffing mix.

title: make your own eggbeaters(this equals 1 whole egg)
directions: This scrambled in nonstick pan tastes very good and is heart safe.

title: fruit kuchen
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut butter into cake mix (dry) until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan, building up slight edges.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chicken l'orange
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry.
Mix next 3 ingredients together in a small bowl.
Spoon mixture over chicken and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or buttered noodles and salad.
Serves 6. This is a great company dish and very easy.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all together and melt in double boiler over low heat. Serve in chafing dish with Fritos.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add orange juice and 1/4 can of water.
Mix well.
To this add drained mandarin orange sections and the pineapple.
Mix.
Place in mold or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set until firm and serve with Cool Whip (which can be diluted with orange juice or pineapple juice).
Or serve on lettuce with a dab of mayo.

title: meat, sausage and cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and onion and drain off grease.
Brown ground meat and drain.
Melt cheese in soup and add tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients and simmer 2 minutes or longer and serve warm with chips.
Can be frozen.
This can be heated in a microwave oven. This is also great in a crock-pot on low heat.

title: asparagus tidbits(appetizer)
directions: Trim bread crusts and roll the bread to flatten. Blend the cheeses and egg.
Spread on each slice of bread.
Roll asparagus spears onto each slice.
Dip into melted butter.
(The bread was rolled with asparagus on it.)
Place rolls on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen slice into 4 quarters.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
This recipe freezes well, but set out 1 hour before baking.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes.
Cut to measure about 4 cups.
Heat 3 tablespoons of butter until melted.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Arrange potatoes in greased casserole, 3 layers, topping each with 1/2 of the onion and 1/3 of the white sauce.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake until potatoes are tender, 60 to 70 minutes longer.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add bananas, milk and flavorings; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir into mixture.
Pour in 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before icing.

title: tropical trail mix
directions: Combine the ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook first four ingredients approximately 4 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix next 5 ingredients well to form sauce.
Next, arrange the shredded cheese.
Then add a layer of melted oleo and crushed crackers.
Now layer broccoli, sauce, cheese and Ritz crackers in layers in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until bubbly.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and add sugar. Add milk slowly. Stir constantly over medium-high heat. Bring to a rolling boil. Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: "don't like liver" liver
directions: Wash and season liver strips.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle bread crumbs over liver.
Place bacon strips over liver. Bake in 350° oven until done (15 to 20 minutes).

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add corn and soup to beef; mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; cover mixture with Velveeta slices.
Finally, top with mashed potatoes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and onion casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli spears according to package directions (leave in cooking pouches).
Place broccoli pouches in large casserole dish.
Drain onions and mix with broccoli spears.
Combine mayonnaise and horseradish.
Spread mixture over top of broccoli and onions.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serves 4.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Blend. Serve over pasta, tomatoes, zucchini or in soup.

title: mary's fudge(may be made weeks ahead and stored in refrigerator.)
directions: Mix sugar, evaporated milk and margarine; bring to a boil. Boil exactly 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and stir in remaining ingredients in order as listed.
(Make sure you add the Marshmallow Creme last and after all other ingredients are well blended.)
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan; let set up. When hardened, cut into small squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine soup, mustard
and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend well. Set aside.	Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, onions and 1/4 cup soup.
Shape into 6 patties.
Brown in skillet.
Drain drippings. Combine
remaining
soup
and
water.
Pour
over browned patties.
Cook
over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: 10 cup cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, peanut butter, sugars and eggs. Follow with flour, soda and baking powder. Stir in coconut, nuts, chips, raisins and oatmeal. Drop on greased cookie sheet from teaspoon. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut-pecan candy
directions: Mix marshmallow cream, coconut and roasted pecans.
Put in refrigerator to chill for 15 minutes.
Roll in small balls.
Dip in chocolate mixture.
Melt dark and white chocolate bark together; mix good.

title: shanghai noodles with spicy beef sauce
directions: Heat skillet.
Add
the
oil,
garlic,	ginger root and pepper flakes.
Saute
seconds.
Add onions; stir-fry until onions are transparent.
Crumble in lean ground beef; stir-fry until meat is light brown.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs and butter.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: You will need a glass rectangular or round pan.
Blend together cream cheese and sugar.
If too stiff, add a little milk to make it easier to spread.
Set aside.
Spread half the Cool Whip in bottom of pan and cut angel food cake into about 18 to 22 slices.
Press half of the cake slices into the Cool Whip and spread cream cheese and sugar mixture over cake slices.
Add remaining cake slices and spread remainder of Cool Whip over cake slices.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pronto pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice until thick.
Add nuts and fruit.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts and chill at least 2 hours.
Keep refrigerated.
Can also be frozen.

title: smoked sausage oleo(by hillshire farms)
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Add tomato sauce, oregano and beans. Simmer five minutes.
Place 2/3 bag of crushed tortilla chips in bottom of a 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Layer one cup of cheese on chips.
Pour sausage mix over cheese.
Layer on remaining chips and one cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until heated through.
Top with sour cream, shredded lettuce and sliced ripe olives, if desired.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in bowl.
Heat margarine, shortening and water in a pan to boil.
Add peanut butter and pour over mixture; mix well.
Beat eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Add to first mixture.
Bake in greased and floured sheet pan in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions in oleo; combine with soups, broth and chili peppers.
Add pieces of chicken and mix well.

title: caramel icing
directions: Take out 5 tablespoons of sugar and caramelize.
Mix remaining sugar, cream and butter and cook until it reaches a boil.
Add caramelized sugar, beating constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage. Cool and beat.

title: mor mors' holiday salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Drain pineapple and use juice for second cup of liquid.
Add cream cheese and dissolve well.
Add fruit.
After cooling and before jelled, add whipped cream.
Chill until set.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a 3-quart heavy saucepan, add sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Cook on medium heat.
Bring to full boil, stirring continually for 5 minutes or until candy thermometer reaches 234° or soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream until melted.
Add peanut butter until mixed well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour immediately into a 9-inch dish that has been sprayed with butter flavored Pam.
Cool at room temperature 4 or 5 hours before cutting.
After cutting into squares, store in an airtight container.

title: silver queen 1-2-3(microwave)
directions: Place whole ear of corn (still in silk and husk) in microwave and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Use a towel to remove from oven. Discard husk and silk.
Add margarine and salt.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together and store in dry place.
Put 1/3 cup of mix to 1 cup boiling water for 1 cup of hot chocolate serving.

title: beef roni
directions: Brown onions in oleo.
Add ground beef and brown lightly.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add macaroni; cover and cook 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook until thick.

title: zero salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar with lid.
Shake well before using.
This dressing may be used in any amount.
Chopped parsley or green pepper, horseradish or mustard, etc. may be added, if desired.
Calories: 0.

title: idaho potato soup
directions: Put potatoes and onion in saucepan.
Cover with water; add salt.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes.
Mash potatoes in their liquid.
Add milk and butter. Stir; if soup is still too thick, add milk.
Keep on medium heat until serving time.
Serves 5.

title: good dessert
directions: Blend margarine, flour and sugar and pat into a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk according to package instructions.
Spread the pudding over the cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar layer.
Put a layer of Cool Whip over the pudding.
Sprinkle 2 cups toasted coconut on top.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Discard all imperfect kernels and put the popped corn into a large pan.
Cook sugar, salt, vanilla, syrup and water to the medium crack stage (280°), stirring constantly.*
Add food coloring; stir again and pour over popcorn (careful, it's hot). While pouring over popcorn, mix and move popcorn around carefully to cover each kernel.

title: easy chicken pan pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 2-quart baking dish.
Place chicken and vegetables in baking dish and stir in soup, broth, pepper and sage.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients with electric mixer.

Then can either bake in candy papers (makes about 4 dozen) at 325° for 25 minutes or can put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of a paper muffin cup, fill 2/3 full and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or top gets golden brown.
Top with small amount of cherry pie filling on each one when cool.

title: lois punch
directions: Make a gallon of cherry Kool-Aid.
Add tangerine juice (frozen), orange juice (frozen) and pre-sweetened Kool-Aid in a gallon size can.
Mix it up real good.

title: crockpot macaroni & cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni, put in crockpot. Stir in cheese. In small bowl whip eggs, canned milk, salt & pepper. Pour over macaroni & cheese; stir. Add the rest of the milk and stir. I usually ad more cheese (mild) on top. Put some butter on top. Cook on low for 3 hours.

title: special meat loaf
directions: Boil sausage about 10 minutes
to rid it of excess fat. Mix sausage, hamburger, egg, bread, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle a piece of waxed paper with bread crumbs.
Spread meat mixture in thin layer over crumbs.
Put
a
slice
of
ham
over this, cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Roll
up
like
a
jelly
roll. Place seam side down in
baking
pan
large enough to accommodate.
Bake at 350° for 45
to 60 minutes.
Let rest for about 20 minutes before slicing.
MmmmGood!
Serves approximately 8. May be frozen if you have leftovers, I never have had any!

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix ingredients together with mixer and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach. Place on paper towel and squeeze until all water is out. Combine spinach, mayonnaise, sour cream and vegetable soup mix. Cover and chill for several hours. Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: danish puff
directions: Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour as for pie crust.
Add 2 tablespoons water;
mix with fork.
Form into a ball.
Divide in half and pat both onto large ungreased cookie sheet.
Make strips, 12 x 4 inches and 1 inch apart.
Put 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup water in pan.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add extract; remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup flour; stir well to keep from lumping.
When smooth and thick, add eggs one at a time (whole); beat until smooth.
Divide in half and spread on prepared crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes, until crisp and brown.
This will be high, but will fall when removed from oven.
Using your favorite frosting recipe, frost each puff, then sprinkle with pecans.

title: basic white sauce
directions: In a 4-cup measure, microwave the butter on High for 45 seconds to 1 minute or until melted. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until mixture is smooth. Blend in the milk.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 5 minutes or until mixture thickens and bubbles, stirring well once or twice during cooking time.

title: ice cream muffins
directions: Combine in mixing bowl flour and ice cream.
Beat until smooth.
Fill well-greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 20
to
minutes
or
until golden brown.
(If a richer muffin is desired, add 1 egg and 2 tablespoons cooking oil.)

title: pineapple pesto potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and dice (with skins on).
Combine syrup, vinegar, oil, salt, garlic and basil.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: summer garden casserole
directions: Wash and dry vegetables but do not peel.
Cut all vegetables into chunks and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot butter throughout casserole.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top of vegetables.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of cheese.
Lightly sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: baked stuffed morels
directions: Quickly wash mushrooms to remove dirt from pits.
Boil for 2 minutes and drain.
Remove and chop stems.
Mix stems, garlic, onion, seasonings and white wine in skillet or saucepan; simmer to blend flavors.
Stir in breadcrumbs and cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon stuffing into cavity of each mushroom and place in a baking dish. Drizzle with butter.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: martha washington buttercreams
directions: Cream butter, sift confectioners sugar and beat into butter until light.
Add vanilla and salt.
Store in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Shape into desired forms, adding nut meats, Brazil nuts or crystallized fruits, if desired.
Dip candy in the chocolate and paraffin which have been melted together over boiling water. After dipping creams into chocolate, set on buttered platter to harden.

title: pork chop meal
directions: Heat oil in a 4-quart pressure cooker.
Season pork chops with salt and pepper; brown on both sides in hot shortening.
Add broth.
Place vegetables on top of pork chops.
Add soup over top. Close cover securely.
Cook 10 minutes at 15 pounds of pressure. Cool quickly under cold running water.
Remove chops and vegetables to a serving platter.
Blend flour and 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to juices in pan.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Serve with chops and vegetables.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix together the carrots and the raisins.
Refrigerate.
At the last minute, stir in the dressing.

title: spinach calzone
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella, spinach and garlic powder in bowl.
Mix and roll out 1 pizza package.
Put 1/2 (or less) of cheese mixture onto bread 1/2 down from top; fold top over.
Crimp edges together; repeat with other package.
Place both calzones onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° approximately 20 to 30 minutes (until golden brown).
Put onto serving trays and slice.
Serve immediately with warmed spaghetti sauce.
Enjoy!

title: one minute bread and butter pickles
directions: Put all ingredients, except cucumbers, in an enameled pan and let come to light boil.
Add cucumbers.
Let come to boil and boil 1 minute.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Seal while hot.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch glass pan in the order given.
Cover with plastic wrap and age overnight in the refrigerator.

title: smoked brisket
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Mix other sauces and marinade.
Lay brisket fat side down in pan and cover tightly with foil and marinate roast overnight in refrigerator.
Next a.m., turn roast over and cover tightly with new foil.
Cook in 225° oven for 6 hours or until brisket is fork tender.

title: raspberry topping
directions: Beat, beat, beat and beat some more!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add grated zucchini and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in loaf pans.
This makes 2 large pans.

title: hotel adler black forest gateau
directions: Spread red currant jelly evenly over 1 layer of chocolate cake, then spread about 3/4 cup whipped cream over the jelly and add the cherries. Place another cake on the top of the cherries and drizzle cherry brandy over it, spread with 3/4 cup cream. Place the third cake on the top. Spread the remaining cream over the top and sides, sprinkle with shaved chocolate and decorate with whole black cherries.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and margarine until well blended.
Set aside 1 cup for streusel topping.
Add 2 eggs and 1 cup milk; beat until smooth.
Add 2 cups blueberries and spoon into paper-lined muffin cups.

title: bean salad
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over beans.

title: classic chocolate souffles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 8 (2/3 cup) souffle dishes. Sprinkle with sugar.
Tap off excess.
Bring milk and 1 cup of sugar to simmer in large saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat to low.
Add chocolate and stir until smooth.
Pour into large bowl.
Cool 10 minutes.
Beat whites into soft peaks. Add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Whisk 1/4 whites and yolks into chocolate mixture.
Fold in remaining whites.
Bake until souffle puffs about 16 minutes.

title: hot wings
directions: Flour and lightly season chicken wings.
Brown and bake at 350°
for 1/2 hour.
Mix chopped garlic, soy sauce, sugar and chopped peppers together in saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook until sauce becomes thick.
Dip cooked wings into sauce coating each piece.
Serve with sour cream or Ranch dip.

title: chocolate-raspberry torte
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Beat butter and sugar with mixer until fluffy. Alternately add flour and egg yolks. Mix in chocolate. Beat egg whites in separate bowl until stiff. Gently stir into chocolate mixture. Grease and flour 9-inch round cake pan. Spoon batter into pan. Bake until brown, about 35 minutes. Cool; remove pan. Split cake in half horizontally. Spread jam over bottom half of cake. Replace top half. Spread frosting on top. Garnish with whipped cream and raspberries. Serves 12.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Take out 2/3 cup of cake mix to be used later.
Mix the rest with melted oleo and egg.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice according to directions on box.
Cook sausage, onion, green pepper and celery until done.
Drain off excess drippings.
Stir rice into sausage mixture. Add soups, mushrooms, pimento and cheese.
Place in casserole dish, 12 x 8-inch. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cherry pie
directions: Prepare pastry; line 9-inch pie plate with one crust.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Drain cherries.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Take about a teaspoon of dough and roll into ball.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.
May add raisins and/or nuts.

title: spaghetti saucewith or without meat
directions: Add all ingredients together in large pot.
Stir well to mix paste.
If using meat, slice sausage into six inch lengths.
Beef brisket can stay whole or for quicker cooking cut into 2 inch wide strips the length of the brisket.
Bring to boil stirring often, then simmer over low heat for 2-3 hours.
Longer cooking adds more flavor and makes meat more tender.
May be frozen and reheated for future meals.
Makes 1-2 meals depending on family size.
Serve over pasta.

title: breakfast surprise pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line unbaked pie shell with half of the cheese, cut into strips.
Top cheese with cooked, crumbled sausage.
Cover with remaining cheese. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; beat well.
Pour over ingredients already in pie shell.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Serve piping hot.
Serves 6.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook mixture of first 5 ingredients to desired doneness.
Then add 8 ounces cream cheese and 2/3 cup milk.
Mix until cream cheese is melted and serve over noodles.

title: tomato celery soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter; do not brown.
Add tomato soup, water, parsley, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Celery will remain crisp.
Top with unsweetened whipped cream and chopped parsley, if desired.

title: lemon pie
directions: In a double boiler heat all ingredients. Pour into pie shell. For the meringue beat egg whites to a stiff peak. Put on top of pie. Bake at 250° until meringue is browned.

title: black walnut icebox cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and butter; add eggs.
Add next ingredients gradually.

Add vanilla, then black walnuts (keep back 2 tablespoons flour to put on nuts so they won't stick together). Roll into 2 rolls; put in refrigerator or freezer overnight. Grease pans; slice cookies very thin.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 10 minutes.
Watch closely; do not overcook.

title: mom's date cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening.
Stir in sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten egg and sliced dates.
Mix well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the elbow macaroni in boiling water until tender; drain. In saucepan, melt the butter.
Blend in the flour, salt and pepper. Add the milk; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add the onion (optional) and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Mix sauce with macaroni.
Bake at 350° in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumber-yogurt salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and quarter lengthwise; cut crosswise into thin slices. Spread cucumber slices in a large shallow dish. Sprinkle with salt; let stand 16 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients, except mint; add cucumber slices and mix well.
Sprinkle with mint. Yield: 8 servings.

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour water and juices into a 30-cup percolator. In the basket, put the brown sugar, spices and salt. Plug in and perk.

title: easy chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Cook chicken; place in baking dish.
Cover with soup, broccoli and cheese in that order.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Cover top with stuffing.
Bake at 375° covered for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: raspberry-pear pie(makes 8 servings)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour, orange peel and cinnamon. Add pears and raspberries; toss to coat. Set aside.

title: frozen punch cubes
directions: Simmer the sugar and water for 5 minutes. Add the orange juice and unsweetened pineapple juice.
Mix well and pour in ice cube trays.
Freeze well.
Just before serving, fill glass with about 3 cubes and pour chilled ginger ale over them.

title: graham nut bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick stuck in the center comes out clean.

title: never fail refrigerator dough
directions: Place yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and water in cup and stir to dissolve; set aside to rise. Warm milk and melt oleo (together). Beat eggs, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk and oleo mixture and then yeast mixture to bowl. Add half the flour and beat with electric mixer until smooth. Add remaining flour and beat with wooden spoon until elastic like.
Put lid on bowl and place in refrigerator overnight or at least 7 hours.

Roll dough out while cold to desired thickness and brush with melted oleo. Sprinkle over top with cinnamon mixture, which is 1 tablespoon sugar to 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Roll up dough and cut into cinnamon rolls.
Let rise 1 to 2 hours.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Butter Frosting while warm.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs, food coloring and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Add vanilla.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 layers.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on bread or crackers.

title: school day cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients, (except oatmeal and rice krispies), together until well blended.
Stir in oatmeal and rice krispies. Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes till light brown.
Freeze well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves. Add to other ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup nuts, if you desire. Grease and flour bottom of loaf pans.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Mix together.
Make in ice cream freezer.

title: memaw king's cornbread
directions: Stir together and bake.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into a large container and freeze thoroughly.
Defrost 20 minutes before serving.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: First, preheat oven to 375°.
Cook lasagne noodles according to package directions.
(Cook the least time recommended so noodles are firm.)
Cook spinach according to package directions. Drain and squeeze dry.
Combine in bowl:
spinach, cottage cheese and egg.

title: tomato-cheese pie
directions: Put tomatoes in pie shell.
Sprinkle with basil, salt, pepper, sugar and onion.
Spread all cheese over tomatoes.
Combine eggs, flour and milk.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 375° (350° for glass), 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: salmon bake dish
directions: In a glass casserole mix together all ingredients except margarine and crushed saltines.
Sprinkle crushed saltines on top and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sugarless sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients well.
Pour in unbaked pie shells. Bake at 450° for
minutes
or until edge of pie crust gets golden brown.
Turn
heat
to
and bake until filling is set, about 30 minutes.
Makes two pies.

title: mock ravioli
directions: Mix all
ingredients, except macaroni, together.
Place layers of macaroni
in greased baking dish.
Top with layer of spinach mixture; repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with meat layer.
Bake
at
for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cornbread, onions, celery and seasonings in large bowl.
Mix well.
Blend in broth, butter and milk. Mixture should be very soft to allow drying during baking.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until browned.
Makes 1 pan.

title: sharon's waldorf salad
directions: Stir together all ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: chile hominy casserole
directions: Combine 1 cup cheese and remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, 1 cup sugar and eggs until fluffy.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, soda and salt thoroughly and add to shortening mixture.
Roll dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Then mix 2 teaspoons sugar with cinnamon and roll balls into cinnamon mixture.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake until cookies are set (about 10 minutes).
Makes 2 dozen.

title: soap suds snow
directions: Slowly add water to flakes in a plastic bowl and whip until dough is of a consistency that can be rolled into snowballs or formed into other shapes.
Tint pink for cotton candy art projects or another color of your desire.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add shortening and mix with fork. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix. Roll out thin and cut into desired shapes. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Yields 4 dozen.

title: stacked enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat; sprinkle with garlic powder and cumin. Add chili powder and flour; make paste.
Add water; cook until it starts thickening like a thin gravy.
Take tortilla and dip in mixture to soften.
Put on plate.
Add a little of the meat mixture if enough doesn't stick to tortilla.
Sprinkle with some onion and cheese.
Repeat as many as you can eat (3 or 4 high).
Top with chopped lettuce and tomatoes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease large cake pan.
Cut dough when thawed into small pieces and place on bottom of pan.
Add brown sugar and pudding alternately until gone.
Add cinnamon and sugar mixture evenly on top and then pour melted butter.
Add nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Put strawberries in hot jello until melted. Add pineapple and chill.

title: ma's hershey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sour cream, nuts and candy.
After batter is well mixed, then add sour cream, nuts and chocolate.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low calorie milkshake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix pie mix and sugar together in a saucepan. Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup milk together and slowly add to dry mixture. Blend well.
When mixture is smooth and well mixed, add remaining 1 1/2 cups milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture thickens and starts to boil.
Remove from heat. Add butter.
Pour into prepared pie crust. Top with meringue and brown in oven.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dove pie
directions: Soak doves in lightly salted water.
Boil until tender. Reserve about 1/2 cup stock.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well (will be thick) and press into an
8 x
8-inch
pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into bars. Spray pan with Pam.
Enjoy!

title: spiced apple muffins
directions: Grease a 12 hole muffin tin.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In a separate bowl, combine the milk, egg and melted margarine.
Add the dry ingredients to the liquid ingredients and mix (batter will be lumpy).
Fold in apples.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over the top of unbaked muffins.
Bake 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan and cool on cooling rack.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds and mayonnaise which should be added just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, cocoa and canned milk.
Bring to boiling point, boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, oats and nut meats. Stir well and pour in buttered dish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together sugar, oil, shredded zucchini, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and ginger.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon cake squares
directions: Cream the oleo with the sugar and add in this order the eggs, flour, baking powder, salt, egg and rind of lemon. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 8 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: good barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and pour over meat.
This sauce is good on chicken and ribs.
I usually double the recipe.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, butter, peanut butter and both sugars.
Add eggs, mixing thoroughly.

title: quick french bread pizza
directions: Split French bread into halves.
Brown hamburger and sausage in large skillet.
When about half browned, add onion and green pepper.
Drain fat.
Spread sauce on both halves.
Top with meat mixture.
Add cheese, mushrooms and olives.
Turn oven on broil. Place bread halves on large cookie sheet and put in center of oven rack.
Allow cheese to melt.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown beef in fat with onion.
Add the other ingredients. Cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: birthday cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, milk and lemon flavoring.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Remove the crusts from bread and set aside.
Arrange bread slices in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken; cover with the mushrooms and water chestnuts.
In a bowl, beat eggs; blend in milk, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over chicken. Arrange cheese on top.
Combine soups and pimientos, pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, crumble crusts; toss with melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325°
for 1 1/4 hours or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pasta with beans and garlic
directions: Slowly heat garlic in melted bacon fat.
Be careful not to burn.
when garlic has softened add chicken broth and celery. Cook until celery is soft.
Cook pasta until done.
Drain.
