Add white kidney beans to celery mixture, heat through.
Do not drain beans.
Add liquid mixture to drained pasta.
Incorporate well. Season to taste with black pepper and salt.
Tastes best after sitting to blend flavors.
Freezes well.

title: beef tips
directions: Place meat in casserole.
Combine soups and pour over meat. Do not season.
Do not cover.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 6.
Easy and delicious, fork-tender.

title: one dish meal
directions: Rub flour, brown sugar, mustard and pepper into ham slice. Place in casserole and arrange potatoes around ham.
Cover with milk and bake in covered dish at 350° until potatoes are cooked.

title: greek chile-cheese pastries
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush baking sheets with melted butter. Beat eggs, cheeses, parsley and salt together until well blended. Stack 2 pastry sheets; cut stacked sheets lengthwise in 3-inch wide strips.
Brush each 2-layer strip with melted butter on both sides, then place a spoonful of cheese filling at one end of each strip.
Top with a few pieces of chile.
Fold one corner of strip over filling to create a triangular end, then fold triangle over on itself.
Continue to fold triangle from side to side until you reach end of pastry strip.
You should have a triangle shaped pastry.
Pierce top of pastry with a wooden pick and place on buttered baking sheet.
Continue to make pastries with remaining filo sheets, cheese filling and chilies.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and flaky.
Makes about 4 dozen pastries. If you prefer a milder flavor, substitute Muenster cheese for the Greek Feta.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix butter, shortening, water and cocoa in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over flour, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in 10 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: baked chicken sandwich
directions: Mix all together.
Spread mix on 8 slices of bread and cover with 8 slices.
Wrap individual sandwiches in foil.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, dip sandwich while still frozen in well-beaten egg, then crushed potato chips.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet. Bake 1 hour or a little more at 300°.
Serve with salad and a light dessert.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add chocolate chips and keep over low heat until chips are melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach crumble
directions: Arrange peach slices in shallow baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: walnut caramels(blue ribbon, california state fair 1974)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add syrup and salt to butter.
Bring to a boil for 7 minutes.
Mix in baking powder; remove from heat and add walnuts.
Mix thoroughly. Butter inside of 8 x 8-inch pan, then place mixture in pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Yields 35 candies.

title: pears mona lisa
directions: Drain pear halves and allow to dry on a towel.
Dip each half in melted chocolate and place on ice cream filled meringue.
Top with whipped cream and store in freezer until 20 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: tofu mexican casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender. Add tomatoes, taco seasoning mix, salt and green chilies.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes. In a
lightly greased 2-quart casserole, arrange 1/2 of each of the following in layers:
tortilla chips, sauce, cheese and tofu. Repeat layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blue ribbon pound cake
directions: Start all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add flavoring.
Alternately add flour (which has been sifted with baking powder) and milk to creamed mixture.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: taco trash
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of a large dish with straight sides or 2 pie pans.
Next spread guacamole or taco salad dressing mix that you mixed with sour cream.
Make in the order above.
If you want it a little spicier, you might use a little taco sauce spread on top of the tomatoes.
Its about 2 inches deep in one casserole.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together the tuna, soup and milk.
Add the noodles and peas.
Smash the potato chips; add to the ingredients.
Sprinkle a half cup of potato chips on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease cookie sheets.

In a small bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Beating at high speed, gradually sprinkle in sugar, a few tablespoons at a time; beat until sugar is completely dissolved. Beat in vinegar and vanilla.
Fold in pecan halves.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart, onto cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cookies remain light.
Remove cookies to cool.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter dessert
directions: Combine crushed cookies and butter.
Reserve 1/4 cup crumb mixture.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes (if using glass pan, at 350°).

title: taco casserole
directions: For crust, mix potatoes, sour cream and water and pat into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until edges start browning.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Using a spoon, mix together sugar, beans and butter.
Add eggs, coconut and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with pecan halves.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: family steak marinade
directions: Mix and pour over steak.
Marinate overnight.

title: orange cake
directions: Grind together raisins and orange peel.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add ground raisins and orange peel.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour mixture and sour milk alternately.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake mix.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Poke holes in cake.
Pour 1 can Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Pour 12 ounce jar caramel topping on top.
Cool in refrigerator.
Top with 8 ounce Cool Whip and Heath candy bar crumbs.

title: cool strawberry-pineapple salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Jell-O. Add yogurt and pineapple.
Mix well with spoon. Place in refrigerator and chill at least 2 to 4 hours.

title: honey braised chicken
directions: Pour oil in hot pan.
Add soy sauce, honey and ginger.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Add chicken; simmer until chicken is shiny and soy sauce is all absorbed.
Serve with rice and vegetables.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk; beat until thick.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with vanilla wafers.
Place sliced bananas on top of wafers.
Pour pudding mixture over bananas.
Top with additional Cool Whip if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: green beans in tomato sauce
directions: Place beans, juice and tomato juice in a pan.
Fry bacon until very crisp; crumble into beans.
In bacon grease, fry onion and garlic until lightly browned; pour over beans.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook early in the day and reheat before serving so flavor of all ingredients is well blended.

title: crispy cookie coffee cakes
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine flour, salt, juice, 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut oleo in with a fork.
Combine eggs, milk and yeast; add to flour mixture.
Combine lightly.
Cover tightly and chill overnight.

title: marie's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
Roll on to well floured surface.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Add icing, if desired.
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove heart of cabbage and cook whole head in boiling water. Mix meat mixture with hands.
Combine hamburger, cooked rice, egg, onion, cooked sausage, some sauerkraut juice and tomato sauce. Cook meat mixture until lightly cooked together.

title: raspberry snow with custard sauce
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Pour into blender. Add ice cubes and egg whites. Blend till ice is dissolved and mixture is triple in volume. Pour into individual dessert dishes and let set in refrigerator. Mix pudding according to package. Spoon pudding on top of jello mixture. Top with a spoonful of cool whip.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pound cake(english)
directions: Sift the dry ingredients.
Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Alternately add the flour mixture and the milk. Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 325° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and carrots with Marzetti slaw dressing until moist.
Slaw will become more moist as it cools in refrigerator.

title: bean salsa soup
directions: Saute sausage 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Drain excess fat. Add tomatoes, beans and cilantro; mix well.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Garnish with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: weight watcher's cheese 'n' eggplant pie
directions: On baking sheet, arrange eggplant slices in a single layer; broil, turning once, for 3 to 5 minutes on each side (slices should be crisp and brown).
Remove eggplant from broiler and set oven temperature at 350°.

title: quiche in hash brown crust
directions: Spray 2 (9-inch) pie plates with Pam.
Press thawed hash browns between paper towel to remove moisture.
Press into bottoms of pie plates to form crust.
Brush with melted margarine, being more generous with top edges.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Fill with layers of cheeses, meat and onions.
Beat milk with eggs and seasoned salt and pour over the top.
Return to oven and reduce heat to 350° for 35 minutes or so.

title: surprise fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for at least an hour.
Serve as a main course or a light dessert.

title: fajitas
directions: Trim excess fat and gristle
from steaks.
Pound steaks to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place steaks
in plastic bag; sprinkle steaks with
lime juice, garlic salt
and
pepper.
Tie
bags securely and marinate in refrigerator 6 to
hours
or overnight.
Drain marinade off steaks and discard marinade.
Broil steaks at medium to medium-high about 2 to 3 minutes per side. Carve against
the grain
into
thin
slices.
Serve steak in warmed
tortilla accompanied
by tomato, onion, guacamole and sour cream.

title: salmon rice casserole
directions: Precook onion, celery and broccoli in microwave for 3 minutes. Combine these ingredients with soup, salmon (drained), cheese and rice.
Mix well.
Cover and microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Layer in a baking pan.
Cover with cheese; heat in oven and serve hot.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine frozen corn, potato, onion, water, bouillon cubes and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until corn and potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the milk and the margarine.
Combine the remaining milk and flour.
Combine milk and flour mixture into corn mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Makes 4 to 6 side dish servings.

title: carrot pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.	Pour
in
pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 450°, then turn oven to 375° for 30 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: Make the same as my white bread recipe, but substitute 6 cups whole wheat flour for 6 cups of the white flour.

title: slumgullion
directions: Brown hamburger, add onion and tomatoes to meat.
Simmer. Mix with cooked macaroni.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook, peel and slice potatoes.
In pan, fry bacon and put on paper towel to cool.
In bacon grease, put onions and saute.
In bowl, mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in vinegar and water until smooth.
Add to onion and crumbled bacon.
Cook until thickened.
Add parsley and celery seed.
Pour over potatoes. Serve warm.

title: italian spaghetti gravy
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients in a large saucepan. Cook slowly for at least 1 hour.
Add prepared meatballs; simmer until meatballs are done.

title: pepper rice
directions: Mix rice, soup and sour cream together.
Top mixture with peppers.
Sprinkle cheese over top of peppers and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat milk or water; add oleo.
Let come to a rolling boil. Add the flour and salt to liquid.
Stir over heat until it leaves the sides of pan and forms a ball.
Remove from fire and let cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one. Put by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Allow about 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 25 to 30 minutes. Test puffs by removing one from the cookie sheet and if it doesn't fall it is done.
Cool.
Cut off top and fill with favorite filling.

title: sunrise cherry pie
directions: Drain
pineapple well, reserving two tablespoons syrup. Cream softened cream cheese, pineapple syrup, vanilla, 1/4 cup pineapple and 1/2 cup pie filling.
Mix until well blended.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; heat cheese and soup.
Add flour. Mix together.
Add rice.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cook at 350° to desired texture.

title: heavenly dirt
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Make pudding (using the 1 1/2 cups of milk).
Add Cool Whip and vanilla.
Mix everything together.
Set aside.

title: crispy chip chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Place chips in a resealable bag and crush. Mix egg and milk. Dip chicken in egg mixture, then roll into crumbs. Place chicken in dish. Sprinkle remaining crumbs over chicken. Slowly pour butter over chicken. Bake 1 hour or until chicken is no longer pink in the center. Makes 6 servings.

title: jellied orange salad
directions: Add juice of half lemon to prepared orange gelatin.
Chill until almost set.
Roll cheese into small balls after softening with cream or milk.
Moisten small molds, put one ball into each mold, fill with gelatin and chill until set.
Turn out on lettuce and arrange white grapes around the edge.
Top with a little dressing.

title: nachos
directions: Crumble and brown beef.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Spread beans in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with beef and sprinkle with chilies.
Cover this with cheese and drizzle taco sauce over.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chopped green onion and olives.
Top with sour cream. Serve as a dip with nacho chips.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown meat and all other ingredients together and heat.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a large pan, bring water, salt and oil to a boil.
Add macaroni.
Boil until macaroni is tender.
Drain; add margarine, cheese (cut up in small pieces) and soup.
Cover until melted. Add evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until slightly brown around edges.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt chocolate, margarine and 2 tablespoons milk.
Pour over crust. Refrigerate until chocolate is firm.
Place sliced bananas over chocolate.
Prepare the pudding mix with 2 3/4 cups milk; spoon over bananas.
Spread whipped topping over top.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef. Add spaghetti sauce. Cook until done.
Cook noodles until done.
Drain noodles.
Layer pan with sauce, then noodles, then cheese.
Follow the steps until all ingredients are gone, then bake for 1 hour until done at 350°.

title: banana sticky buns
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 2 teaspoons brown sugar, 2 teaspoons butter and 3 pecan halves in each of 12 muffin cups.
Place in oven to melt.
Remove.
Stir Bisquick and bananas together. Smooth into a ball.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into a rectangle, 15 x 19-inches.
Spread with 2 tablespoons butter; sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Roll up tightly, beginning at wide end.
Cut into 12 (1 1/4-inch) slices.
Place in cups.
Bake 10 minutes. Immediately invert pan on baking sheet for a minute.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Place 1 wafer in bottom of cupcakes liner.
Beat all ingredients together with mixer.
Fill cupcakes using all batter and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with your favorite pie filling, fresh fruit or frozen fruit.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating mixture well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to combined cream mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch baking tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 or 40 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing from pan and cool.

title: eggless cake
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Add soda, salt and spices.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add salt in flour, 1/3 at a time. Alternate with milk.
Add raisins.
Add vanilla.
Beat well after each.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch or 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook beef and onion together until onions are tender and drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer slowly 30 minutes or more.
Add more seasonings if needed.
Makes a big pot of soup. This is good leftover or it may be frozen.

title: sugar cured ham
directions: Dampen with water the pepper, salt and sugar so it sticks to the meat when you rub it on, then put it in a large brown paper or bag.
Tie a cloth around it and hang it up in the smokehouse.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Put cranberries through a meat grinder.
Pare orange; remove seeds.
Trim off any white membrane.
Put orange rind and pulp through meat grinder.
Mix sugar, berries and orange together. Chill a few hours (3 to 4) before serving.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Simmer chicken in water with onion, stalk of celery, salt and pepper for 1 hour; cool and slice into pieces.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice, mustard and water chestnuts.
Layer in casserole dish:
broccoli, chicken, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with bread crumbs and melted butter.
You can also use Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add water (enough to cover the shrimp).
Add shrimp.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
It is done when the shrimp turns pink.
Drain and cool with water.
Peel and clean shrimp.
In glass pan (9 x 13-inch), alternate shrimp with layers of onions.
Add bay leaves with sauce.

title: apple cole slaw
directions: Mix lemon juice, mayonnaise and sugar together. Mix all other ingredients, then toss with mayonnaise mixture. Serve chilled. (Sunflower seeds or pine nuts can be added as taste prefers.)

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; add onions, green peppers and oil.
Add all the spices, seasonings, tomato sauce, ketchup and water.
Simmer until thick, about 1 hour.
Cook 1 package lasagna according to the package.
I add 1 tablespoon oil to water so noodles don't stick. Layer noodles, then sauce (about 1 1/2 cups per layer), then Mozzarella cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan, 3 layers high.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Mix together and spread carefully on top of lettuce.
Top with bacon bits (either Bac*Os or crumble fried bacon).
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
This salad keeps well into the second or third day.

title: boiled custard
directions: Heat milk until it's too hot to stick your finger into (do not let it boil).
Beat eggs and sugar together until foamy.
Pour quickly into hot milk, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and will coat a spoon about 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool and refrigerate.
The custard will get thicker as it cooks.

title: molded salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add cranberry sauce and stir.
Add small can crushed pineapple; add cut-up apple.
Pour into mold.

title: quick peach dessert
directions: Drain peaches and put in buttered 8-inch square baking dish. Crumble piecrust mix and sugar together and blend well.
Sprinkle on top of peaches and dot generously with butter.
Bake in preheated slow oven (325°) for 30 minutes, or until brown and bubbly on top.
Serve warm with cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: whole wheat chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon together in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, bring cocoa, water and oil to a boil.

Pour over flour mixture and mix 1 minute, scraping bowl. Dissolve soda in the buttermilk, adding to mixture in bowl, along with the eggs and vanilla. Mix an additional 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan, 10 x 15 x 1-inch. Bake 20 minutes. Ice cake, if desired, while it is still slightly warm. Cool cake before cutting.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat until thick the eggs and sugar.
Combine melted oleo, flour, cocoa, vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Mix well and add to egg-sugar mixture.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Spread jar of marshmallow cream over top immediately after removing from oven.
Let it set a little while. While cake is still warm, put on frosting.

title: gramma's galumkis(cabbage rolls)
directions: Soak head of cabbage in hot water for 4 to 5 hours, removing stem and any outer leaves that are torn or brown first.
Remove cabbage from water and separate leaves; set aside until stuffing is mixed.
Mix beef, rice, eggs, milk, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper until thoroughly combined.
Place enough of mixture in cabbage leaf to fill half full.
Fold ends of cabbage over mixture; secure with a toothpick, if necessary.
Repeat procedure with remaining leaves (until too small).
Place cabbage rolls seam side down in greased baking dish (size will vary with the amount of galumkis being made).
Pour sauce over top of rolls. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a medium bowl, combine soups, 1/4 cup butter and rice. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces over rice mixture.
Brush with remaining butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 275° for about 2 1/2 hours until chicken is tender.

title: party wieners
directions: Mix jelly and mustard.
Add hot dogs; let stand for 15 or 20 minutes.
Skewer each piece with toothpick and place on platter. Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes on High.
Serve while hot.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add scalded milk (cooled) and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir in melted shortening, cooled. Add beaten egg and salt; slowly stir in flour until dough is stiff enough to knead.
Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic for 10 minutes.
Make dough into ball; place in a large greased bowl.
Brush top with melted shortening.
Cover and keep in warm place until dough doubles in size.
Turn out onto floured board; knead slightly and form into rolls.
Place in baking pan.
Brush with shortening.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake in the oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: smoky cheese ball
directions: Bring cheeses and margarine or butter to room temperature. Add milk and steak sauce; beat with electric mixer until fluffy. Cover; chill in refrigerator for at least 4 hours or up to 24 hours. Shape mixture into ball. Roll in nuts. Let stand for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: lime and horseradish salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add enough water to juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Add to Jell-O and heat until dissolved (do not boil). Set aside to cool slightly.
Mix cottage cheese, pineapple, milk, mayonnaise, nuts and horseradish, then add to Jell-O.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch container and chill until solid.
Yields about 18 servings.

title: amish hamburger "goop"
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Drain.
Add mushrooms and soup.
Mix thoroughly.
Top with grated cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts. Serve with or on top of mashed potatoes or egg noodles.
Good with side dish of green beans or salad.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, spices and baking soda in bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cereal.
Fold in eggs and applesauce and stir just until flour is moistened.
Pour into 2 greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans or four 5 x 2-inch baby loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and finish cooling on rack.

title: easy fruit crisp
directions: Put the can of fruit pie filing in a small baking dish. Spread the Jiffy cake mix on top of the fruit filling.
Dot butter or margarine on the cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix chopped cabbage and salt together.
Let stand 1 hour. Squeeze out juice.
Add carrot and pepper, while cabbage is standing.
Make syrup of vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring syrup to a boil.
Cook for 1 minute.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix and place in containers to freeze.
This can be thawed and refrozen several times.

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in drippings very finely and add milk.
Put onto floured board and knead very lightly.
Roll and cut out.
Bake at 425° until good and brown.

title: easy salad
directions: Place pineapple or peach half on a piece of lettuce.
Mix Cool Whip and mayonnaise together; place on fruit, then put grated cheese on top.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix margarine and crushed corn flakes.
Place half the mixture in greased casserole.
Place cabbage and onion on top of corn flake mixture.
Combine soup, milk, mayonnaise and seasonings and pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle casserole with cheese and remaining corn flakes.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gum drop cake
directions: Dissolve soda in applesauce.
Mix ingredients in order in the regular way.
Add dates and nuts as near whole as possible.
Line loaf pans with wax paper.
Place batter in bottom of pan and them drop the gumdrops, so they don't touch pan.
Bake in moderate oven about 45 minutes. 350°.

title: white almond bark
directions: Mix together in oblong cake pan and cut into pieces.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Dip chicken into egg, then in flour, salt and pepper mixture. Melt butter in large skillet.
Place chicken into skillet and brown.
Remove and set aside.
Place rice, chicken broth, parsley, salt and water in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken and cover.
Lower to simmer for 30 to 45 minutes or until water is absorbed.

title: italian style lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add next 3 ingredients and onion. Mix well.
Add all spices.
If sauce is too dry, add water or more tomato sauce.
Let simmer while preparing the cheese mixture and noodles.

title: german red cabbage(sweet and sour)
directions: Combine the above ingredients.
Cover tightly and steam until the cabbage is tender (several hours).
After the cabbage is cooked, add about 2 tablespoons flour and stir.
Cook until the mixture is thickened.
Add more flour if necessary.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Simmer in skillet 4 minutes, or until mixture spins a thread from spoon.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans.
Stir until syrup turns to sugar, coating all pecans. Separate pecans while cooling.

title: onion and garlic chicken
directions: Mix garlic, parsley, olive oil and seasonings in bowl.
Cut up onion.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Combine and bring to boil, margarine, oil, Coca-Cola and cocoa.
Add to sifted ingredients and mix well.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Pour into batter and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add marshmallows and vanilla.
pour into 9 1/2 x 13 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pan burritos
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a saucepan and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, brown beef in a skillet and drain.
Mix 1/3 of the sauce with the browned beef.
In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, layer the casserole as follows:

1/3 sauce mix, 3 tortillas (torn to fit bottom of pan), 1/2 meat mixture, 1 1/2 cups cheese, 3 tortillas (torn to fit bottom of pan), refried beans spread evenly, remaining meat mixture, 1 1/2 cups cheese, 3 tortillas (torn to fit bottom of pan), remaining sauce and 1 cup cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve with taco sauce, sour cream, chili peppers, chopped onions and/or guacamole, if desired.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix ground beef, onions and peppers.
Brown and drain.
Mix cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, cottage cheese and 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese and tomato sauce.
Cook noodles.
Make layers of noodles, meat and sauce; repeat until ingredients run out.
Add the remaining cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
When done, add 1 teaspoon of garlic powder or oregano on top.

title: pork tenderloins
directions: Brush tenderloins with butter, garlic and spices; place in shallow roaster on rack.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread jam mixed with bourbon or brandy on tenderloins; bake another 15 to 20 minutes, or 160° on meat thermometer. Thicken juices slightly; serve over sliced meat.
Serves 6.

title: no-crust cheese pie
directions: In mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, 2/3 cup sugar and almond extract until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat at low speed after each.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Stir sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of pie.
Chill until serving time.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium mixing bowl. Beat by hand (about 50 strokes). Pour in greased oblong pan. Bake 25 minutes at 325° or 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle miniature marshmallows over brownies. Bake for 5 more minutes. Remove from oven and pour icing over brownies.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Mix sugar, salt, margarine and corn syrup in a medium bowl. Bring to a boil in microwave then cook for another 2 minutes.
Put popped corn in grocery bag with syrup mix and cook 1 1/2 minutes on High in microwave.
Remove bag; shake, cook for 1 1/2 minutes. Pour on large pan to cool.
Stir until dry.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins and set aside.
Add sugar, flour, salt and oleo to raisins.
Return to stove and cook on medium heat until mixture thickens, about 12 to 15 minutes.
The mixture now looks clear.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.
Wait 1 hour before cutting.

title: western relish
directions: Combine salt, pepper, dry mustard and sugar.
Add salad oil and vinegar; mix well.
Pour over cabbage, minced onion, green pepper and carrot.
Toss all together.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425° while you make your crust.
Sprinkle onion, ham, cheese and broccoli in crust.
Beat remaining ingredients until blended; pour over ham mixture.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300° and bake about 30 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter clusters
directions: Place corn syrup, chocolate chips and sugar in saucepan over medium heat.
Cook, stirring frequently, until bubbles break the surface.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; mix until smooth. Stir in Cheerios until coated.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper, forming clusters.
Cool.

title: old fashioned cabbage soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until nearly tender.
Add cabbage and chopped parsley; simmer 5 minutes.
Add flour, blending well.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add stock gradually, mix.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add sliced frankfurters, cooked peas, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Yields 13 (8-ounce) servings.

title: artichoke and spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to directions; drain.
Saute onion in butter; mix all ingredients together (except cheese).
Place in casserole, stir in cheese (retain 1/4 cup).
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: pretzel surprise
directions: Allow margarine to melt and then combine with pretzels in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Form a base and bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: mexican jackpot cheese
directions: Place chilies in bottom of a 7 x 10-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs lightly and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over chilies.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into small squares to serve.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Cool Whip.
Put in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip after cake has cooled.
Decorate with cherries for a festive Christmas cake.

title: erene's chocolate pie
directions: Cook at 400° until golden brown.

title: peanut patties(candy)
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to a soft ball stage, about 5 minutes.
Stir the powdered sugar and food coloring into the mixture.
Drop spoonfuls of mixture onto wax paper.

title: cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make diagonal cuts in the top of the loaf about 3-inches long, 1 1/2-inches deep and 1 1/2-inches apart. Slice the cheeses into 2 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Insert 1 strip of each cheese into each slice made in the bread.
Wrap the loaf in aluminum foil, leaving the top exposed.
Melt the butter over low heat in a 1-quart saucepan.
Stir in the poppy seed, mustard, green onions and lemon juice.
Drizzle the mixture over the bread.
Bake for about 35 minutes or until the cheese melts.
Slice the bread and serve warm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix all but the oleo and vanilla together and cook over medium heat.
When thickened, add the oleo and the vanilla.
Let cool. Place vanilla wafers in a dish and slice bananas over the wafers. Pour the pudding over the bananas and top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise, soup, curry powder and lemon juice.
Stir to smooth sauce.
Mix dressing mix with margarine.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in a 10-inch skillet.
Sprinkle brown sugar over this.
Place pineapple slices, cherries and nuts in the skillet.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Then add milk, shortening and vanilla to the flour mixture.
Beat well and then add the egg.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over pineapple slices in skillet.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Invert quickly onto place.

title: shrimp linguini
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add cloves of garlic, finely chopped.
Add cleaned shrimp (large).
Cook until pink (do not overcook).
Add Newman's marinara sauce and heavy cream.
Stir together.
Add cooked, flat linguini.
Serve.

title: angel food icebox cake
directions: Cut angel food cake in slices.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Spread 1 can cherry filling on top of cake.
Put another layer of angel cake.
In a bowl, put sour cream, vanilla pudding and milk; beat until creamy.
Spread on cake layer.
Top with Cool Whip lite.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate for 5 hours. Serve cold and scoop out.
Can also be made in a trifle bowl.

title: oriental rice
directions: In large frying pan, heat oil.
Add scallions and cook over high heat for 30 seconds, stirring until wilted. Add remaining ingredients except for margarine, cooking and stirring 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine.
Serves 4.

title: crab mousse
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Dissolve gelatine in boiling water and add to soup.
Cool.
Blend or beat with mixer mayonnaise into cream cheese.
Add to cool tomato mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into oiled (spray Pam) 6 cup mold.
Chill overnight.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Spread 3 cups cabbage in bottom of 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Saute onions in small amount of fat.
Add ground beef and cook.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread meat and rice mixture over cabbage.
Top with other 3 cups of cabbage. Spread tomato soup over the top.
Sprinkle with celery seed; cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: breakfast before
directions: Saute sausage and onion.
Drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and dry mustard.
Layer the bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Spray your pan before baking with nonstick spray.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and take out stems.
Mix cream cheese until creamy.
Add bacon bits, chopped onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Chop stems; saute and add to cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into mushroom caps.
Bake just long enough to brown lightly on top.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute butter and uncooked rice.
Add soup, consomme and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: peas and cucumbers
directions: Cut cucumber lengthwise in fourths, then crisscross into 1-inch pieces.
Bring cucumber, peas and water to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until peas are tender (about 10 minutes). Drain.
Stir in lettuce, margarine, sugar, salt and pepper; heat until lettuce is hot.
Mix sour cream and lemon juice; toss with vegetables.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and mix with other ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake 1
hour at 350°. Insert table knife into center of pie.
If it comes out clean, pie is done.
This is a rich pie similar to cheese pie.

title: taco mix
directions: Melt oleo and saute onion and garlic.
Add meat and cook until browned.
Add rest of ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, approximately 15 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 tacos.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients, cutting in shortening.
Add mashed potatoes.
Add enough milk to make firm dough, but not too stiff. Roll out on floured board, then cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased biscuit pan. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes until browned.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cream butter, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add oatmeal mixture, after mixing all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Cool cake 15 minutes.

title: raisin celebration cookies
directions: Rinse and drain raisins; cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolk and flavorings and blend well.
Sift flour and salt and blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven (400°) 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to cool 2 or 3 minutes.
With spatula, remove carefully to wire rack to cool.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash potatoes; pare thinly and remove eyes.
Shred enough potatoes to measure 4 cups.
Drain well.
In small mixing bowl, beat egg until thick and lemon colored.
Mix in potatoes, onion, flour and salt.
Brush skillet lightly with oil.
Heat skillet over low heat.
Shape potato mixture into 8 patties; place into skillet.
Cook over medium heat, turning once, about 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in oil; add onion, garlic and seasonings.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water; add to meat.
Simmer until meat is tender. Add tomatoes and green pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch mix.
Serve over hot noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy tea cakes
directions: Cream together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar when taken out of oven.

title: easy layered casserole
directions: Layer potatoes evenly in oiled baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
Spread corn over the potatoes.
Sprinkle with green pepper, onion and carrots.
Crumble beef over the top. Sprinkle with marjoram and additional salt and black pepper.
Top with the tomato sauce; spread evenly.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: chocolate nut coconut cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Melt chocolate and add the rest of the ingredients to it.
Don't beat, just mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: fresh pesto
directions: Combine fresh leaves and garlic in a food processor.
Blend into a fine paste, scraping sides often.
Add walnuts and cheese. Process until smooth, but slightly grainy.
Pour olive oil through feed tube slowly with machine running.
Mix until smooth.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
Use within one month.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fruit burst cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in almond extract.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Shape level tablespoons of dough into balls; roll in nuts.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Combine Ranch dressing and dill weed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in warm oven at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° or until firm.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook hard 1 hour.
Seal while hot.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain all fruit, except pineapple.
Arrange in Pyrex dish, ending with pineapple chunks and juice.
Slice the butter over the fruit.
Sprinkle fruit with mixture of brown sugar, curry, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Fry bacon or sausage
well and drain. Set aside.
Spray Pam on 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Trim crusts on bread and butter each slice. Put buttered side down until the pan is covered.
Then add	your filling
(bacon or sausage) and 1 cup of the grated cheese.
Then layer
bread
with	butter	side
up
on top of filling.
Mix eggs
and milk;
add seasonings.
Pour over the bread.
Spread cream
soup
on
top.
Cover
and
refrigerate overnight.
Bake in	350° oven 1 hour.
Remove from oven, top with
cheese
and paprika.
Bake
15	minutes longer or until cheese	is
melted. Cut
into
squares.
For Brunch or a Luncheon,
variations	of chicken and seafood can be used for the filling.

title: plate pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together in pie plate.
Pat out to fit pie plate.
Add pie filling.

title: spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, mix water and cornmeal.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm. Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Beat thoroughly; pour into a well-greased pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Serve as an alternative to bread.

title: chinese vegetables with pasta
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix can of whole cranberries and cranberry sauce together. Add strawberry preserves and mix.
Mix jello and hot water together until jello is dissolved.
Add ice cubes.
When melted, mix 1 package gelatin with small amount water until dissolved. Add to jello.
Add mixture to strawberry mixture and chill.
Put nuts in last, if so desired.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and salt.
Add to dry ingredients the nutmeats, raisins, applesauce, melted butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven until done, about 20 minutes for cupcakes and 45 minutes for loaf.

title: waldorf salad with turkey and apricot
directions: Combine the apricot preserves, nonfat yogurt, chopped herbs or curry powder, mustard, lemon juice, lemon zest, salt and pepper in a large mixing bowl.
Stir with spatula until the sauce is well blended.
Add the cubes of turkey or chicken, diced apples, celery and raisins.
Stir to coat the salad ingredients.
Correct the seasoning with more salt and pepper as needed.
Place a lettuce cup on each of 6 serving plates.
Spoon a mound of the salad on each plate.
Garnish each salad with fresh chopped parsley or chives.

title: milky way pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs and candy bars; beat thoroughly.
Add flour, mixed with baking powder, 1 teaspoon at a time, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla flavor. Pour into greased pan; bake at 325°.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel the cucumber and cut it across in two. Then slice them in very thin pieces. Put the sliced cucumber pieces in salt water, let it remain for a few minutes, then squeeze out all the water and put the cucumber into a dish; add the rest of ingredients and mix well together.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Basic Recipe:
To 1 package cake mix, add 2 eggs and 3 tablespoons cooking oil.
Dump in mixer and mix well.
Cook on cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in order listed, grease and flour three 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add enough water to pineapple syrup to equal 2 cups liquid.
In a saucepan, combine gelatin and sugar.
Gradually add pineapple liquid to gelatin-sugar mixture.
Heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin and sugar dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice; chill until partially set.
Fold in crushed pineapple, cranberry-orange relish, celery and walnuts.
Chill until firm.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O as directed on package.
Add pineapple and cool until half jelled.
Whip with hand mixer; add cream cheese. Beat until fairly smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: brown edge cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients and roll into balls.
Flatten.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until browned.

title: spinach appetizer
directions: Cook as directed chipped spinach; drain.
Add 1/4 cup minced onion, bread crumbs, egg, Parmesan cheese and melted oleo.
Form into inch balls.
Freeze overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Fry onions in butter until golden brown.
Soak bread in 1/2 cup milk.
Combine ground meat with fried onions, soaked bread, eggs, salt and pepper.
Roll into 1-inch balls and fry in butter or oil until evenly browned.
Shake pan often to keep ball round. Remove meatballs; add flour to fat and blend.
Add bouillon and milk; cook until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Add meatballs; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: shaving cream bath paint
directions: Squirt shaving cream into each section of a muffin tin.
Add couple of drops of food coloring into each section and mix.

title: fruit square
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda and salt.
Spread 1/2 the batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread pie filling over batter.
If desired, sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg over pie filling before adding top batter.
Spoon out remaining filling for easier spreading.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
When cool, frost with vanilla frosting, or serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: mealtime zucchini fritters(makes 2 servings)
directions: In a blender container, combine all ingredients, except zucchini.
Blend until smooth.
Pour mixture into a bowl.
Drain zucchini in paper towels.
Stir into egg mixture.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir and boil together the sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Add berries and boil 5 more minutes until berries pop.
Add apple and orange rind.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, vinegar and sugar together.
Add to broccoli, cauliflower, chipped bacon, shredded cheese and onion. Refrigerate.

title: noodles and mushrooms
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil until clear.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese and pour into casserole.
Chill. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: You will need a 3 x 9-inch spring-form pan.
(If you don't have one, look in the yellow pages under Restaurant Equipment and Supplies.)

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots, celery and onion until tender.
Add butter.
Add flour to milk; add cheese and cook until cheese is melted.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel
and
cube
eggplant.
Cook covered in water until tender.
Saute diced onions, peppers and celery in oleo.
Mash eggplant
in pan with water.
Add crumbled corn bread and egg. Add remaining ingredients (excluding cheese and soup).
Place in greased
casserole	dish.
Top with cheese.
Place in oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Heat soup, use as sauce over casserole.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine ingredients; spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple-cinnamon muffins
directions: Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Beat egg slightly in medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients, just until moistened.
Divide batter into cups.
Bake until golden brown, 15 to 18 minutes.

title: fish soup
directions: Place onions, celery, salt, fish and butter in large saucepan. Add milk and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Add sour cream, pickle and horseradish.
Add Velveeta cheese. Stir until melted.
Thicken with flour, if desired. Serve.

title: slaw
directions: Mix chopped cabbage, bell pepper and onion together.
Stir in pimento.
Place oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed in pan. Bring to a boil. Boil about 3 minutes.
Pour over slaw mixture. Double recipe if you need to.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green peppers, celery, carrots and onion. Let stand in cold water and salt for 1 hour.
Boil sugar, vinegar and 1/2 cup water.
Drain vegetables.
Pour cooled boiled mixture over cabbage and chill.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower, broccoli and onion into bite size pieces.

title: taco salad(meatless)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Doritos.
Add them just before serving.
(Celery, cucumber or black olives may also be added if desired.)

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package; cool, then drain and squeeze out all liquid.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: crispy lemon pepper baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken and cut up into pieces. Mix crushed corn flakes, lemon pepper seasoning and salt.
Dip chicken into milk, then dip into corn flake mixture until completely coated.
Place on a rack over a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: freddie's casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add beef, salt and pepper.
Heat; do not brown.
Spread part of cabbage in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with more cabbage.
Alternate until all is used.
Pour tomato soup over top.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Put ice cream in dessert bowls.
Store in freezer.
In large saucepan, mix cherries with juice, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Stir over low heat until clear and slightly thick.
Add brandy and Kirsch.
Pour cherries and sauce over ice cream.
Serve.

title: orange balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add orange juice, crumbs and nuts. Pinch off small pieces and make into balls.
Roll in coconut. Refrigerate until firm.
Makes about 72 balls.

title: pasta ala williams
directions: Chop
green
peppers
and
onion.
Cook in 1 tablespoon olive oil
until	softened.
Cook
noodles
as directed, then drain noodles.
Add
a little sauce to the bottom of the pan. Add a layer of noodles, then sauce, then onion and peppers and pepperoni and
layer of cheese.
Layer again, then cover with Mozzarella. Bake
at 375° for about 1 hour or until cheese is brown.
Serve with Italian bread.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage
in
skillet;
drain
well
and
crumble. Pour off drippings, reserving just enough to saute onion, bell pepper and celery, just
until tender.
Add rice, soup mix and salt to boiling
water;
stir until thickened.
Cover and cook 20 minutes on low
heat.
Mix with sausage and sauteed vegetables.
Pour into greased
casserole.
Sprinkle almonds on top and drizzle with melted
butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, until brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir soup, milk and pepper.
Alternate layers of potatoes, onion, sauce and cheese.
Put butter and paprika on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered, then uncover and bake 15 more minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with sliced zucchini.
Peel and cut tomato chunks to cover zucchini.
Dice onions; sprinkle over tomatoes.
Add layer of Velveeta cheese.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into a large bowl.
Bring to a boil:
butter, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture and mix. In another bowl combine well-beaten eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°. Frost hot cake.

title: dilled potato salad with wurst
directions: Cut boiled potatoes into thick slices.
In skillet, over medium heat, cook bacon.
Add celery, onion and pickles.
Cook, stirring, until tender (3 to 5 minutes).
Stir in potatoes, knockwurst, pickle liquid, sugar, caraway seed, mustard and salt. Cover and cook over low heat, turning potatoes occasionally, until tender (10 minutes).
Knockwurst may be cooked separately.
Serves 4.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt all except Rice Krispies on medium heat.
Cook 5 minutes or until gooey.
Add Rice Krispies, one cup at a time.
Cook a couple of minutes.
Cool enough to handle.
Butter hands.
Shape into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix well.
Use "star" in cookie press and press out on a cookie sheet.
Cook about 10 minutes at 400°.

title: j. b.'s chili
directions: Brown ground beef on medium-high.
Then stir in (thoroughly) the remainder of ingredients.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Blend cracker crumbs and butter for topping.
Top the mixture with cracker crumbs and butter combination.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (freezes well).

title: marinara sauce
directions: Brown sausage.
Add onion and garlic.
Herbs may be added at this time to enhance the flavor.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 2 to 4 hours.
Yield:
3 to 4 meals.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch together.
Cook on low heat until mixture becomes clear, remove from heat.
Add strawberry jello mix.
Place strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries; let chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: paper bag apple pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, cook peaches and honey in butter for 5 to 7 minutes until tender.
In mixing bowl, beat cream, confectioners sugar and peach Schnapps until soft peaks form.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat together sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Add and mix together lemon juice.
Add milk and egg whites (fold in).
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: microwave nutty apple
directions: Into 4 glass cupcake pans, place each apple.
Sprinkle core cavity of each apple with 1/4 teaspoon brown sugar.
Fill each with 1 1/2 teaspoons peanut butter and top each with 1/4 teaspoon brown sugar.
Sprinkle each apple with an equal amount of cinnamon and microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Brown beef and onion in shortening.
Remove from heat and add taco sauce, beans and cooked rice.
Mix well. Transfer to baking dish and cover with slices of cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine sliced squash, onion and salt and soak 3 hours in 2 to 3 trays of ice cubes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drain squash and onion.
Add to vinegar mixture and bring back to boil.
Pack in jars while hot.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini into 1/2-inch slices and cook in water for 8 minutes.
Drain and add mixture of soup, cheese, sour cream, carrot, onion, salt and pepper.
In separate bowl, mix stuffing mix and 1 stick margarine, melted.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken

title: chess-pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given; pour in unbaked crust and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: four cheese-cheese ball
directions: Soften all cheese.
Blend together and form into ball.
Roll ball in pecans and parsley.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Bring 3 cups water to a boil; add orange Jell-O and tapioca pudding.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into a mixing bowl.
Cook for 2 hours at 225°.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cocktail cheese biscuits
directions: Cream butter; add shredded cheese, then salt, pepper and flour. Roll into small balls and press pecans on each to flatten.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Yields 40 to 45 biscuits.

title: snappy pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine gingersnap crumbs and butter.
Press into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Saute onions and celery.
Add margarine until soft.
Drain broccoli and chop.
Add onions and celery to Minute rice, cheese and soup.
(I saute the onions and celery in the margarine that the recipe calls for.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: beef and bean sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet; drain.
Stir in beans and barbecue sauce.
Simmer about 15 minutes or until thickened.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: 7 cup fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, then serve chilled.
Flavor improves in the refrigerator.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese and Ro-Tel in crock-pot.
Add sausage.
Heat and serve with chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and apples together.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix in slightly beaten egg and oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients, raisins and walnuts.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: walnut cluster cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a large bowl.
At high speed, mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy. At low speed, mix in melted chocolate and flour mixture.
Fold in walnuts.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: strawberries with white chocolate custard sauce
directions: In bowl, whisk yolks and sugar. In saucepan, bring cream, milk and vanilla bean to a boil. Gradually whisk hot cream mixture into yolk mixture. Return this mixture to saucepan; over medium heat, stir constantly with heat-resistant rubber spatula, 3 minutes until thick enough to coat spatula (do not let boil). Remove from heat. Add chocolate, stirring to melt. Strain through fine sieve into bowl. Remove bean; scrape out seeds into sauce. Place bowl in large bowl filled with ice cubes and water. Stir sauce until very cold. Place strawberries in 6 dessert glasses. Spoon 3 tablespoons custard sauce over each serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add orange juice and remaining ingredients.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan and set in refrigerator. Cut in squares to serve.
This is the salad served at our bazaar at Drummond Chapel.

title: ham-noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles; drain.
Meanwhile, melt 2 tablespoons butter over low heat; stir in flour until smooth. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Add noodles, salt, ketchup, horseradish, ham and peas.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with melted butter and crumbs.
Bake uncovered 35 minutes or until crumbs are brown.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix.
Pour into pie crust.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook 10 minutes, then cook at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Lay steak out flat.
Mix all ingredients, except soup, thoroughly.
Spread on steak and roll up like a jellyroll.
Secure with toothpicks and place in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with undiluted soup. Return to oven for an additional 10 minutes.

title: aunt betty's black chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add cocoa into 2 cups boiling water. Cook on low until slightly thick.
Stir constantly.
Cool for 5 minutes, then add in a large mixing bowl, sugar, vanilla, eggs and oil.
Beat well.
Add flour and baking powder.
Beat well.
Put baking soda in a cup and add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Stir well. Add to batter.
Beat well.
Pour into a well greased and floured cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: fast 'n fun pasta pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine hot pasta, eggs, 1/2 can French fried onions and the Parmesan cheese.
Spread pasta mixture over greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with ground beef mixture and desired toppings.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and remaining onions. Bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: meatballs, rice and gravy
directions: Knead onion soup in ground beef.
Roll the beef into meatballs and brown in Dutch oven; drain fat off meatballs.
Add 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of milk to meatballs.
Let simmer about 1 hour.
Turn heat off.
Let set for another hour.
This is one recipe that the longer it sets the better it tastes.
Serve meatballs on bed of rice and don't forget the gravy.

title: belle helene(chocolate strawberry dip)
directions: Heat whipping cream until hot (do not boil!).
Remove from heat, add chocolate and stir until melted.
Stir in extract and rind, chill.
Can be stored and is delicious on ice cream.

title: mexican salad
directions: Line salad bowl with drained beans. Layer chopped onion over beans.
Layer chopped bell pepper over onion.
Layer chopped tomatoes over bell pepper.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: mama's hamburger dish
directions: Make hamburger into patties.
Flour and brown them in a small amount of oil.
Set meat aside.
Slice onions and set aside.
Crush tomatoes and put them into the skillet.
Layer other ingredients in the pan and cover with water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
(Flour on the patties will make the gravy.)
Yields 6 servings.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet with onion, garlic and green pepper. Add tomato paste, tomatoes, chili powder, oregano, parsley and kidney beans. Salt and pepper to taste. Add in the bouillon cubes and cabbage. Slowly add desired amount of water. Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat and simmer for one hour.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix with all other ingredients and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: sherry casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except breasts). If you want the mixture thinner, add 1/2 cup milk.
Put chicken breasts in baking pan.
Pour mixture over breasts.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: cinnamon rolls with sour cream
directions: Mix and let rise until double in bulk.
Roll out and cover with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon, nuts or raisins.
Roll up and cut.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost. (If you use sweet cream or canned milk, omit the soda.)

title: cornbread stuffings
directions: Saute onions, celery and oleo until tender.
Mix all together, mixing well!

title: kaik-sesame cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Roll small amount, enough to fit in palm of hand, into an oblong roll and form into donut shape.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° about 10 minutes.
Then brown lightly in broiler.
Should make about 5 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle top with paprika. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake as directed on box.
Cool for 1/2 hour.
Using the handle of a wooden spoon, poke several holes close together.
Mix Eagle Brand and caramel topping; pour over cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Break Heath bars into pieces and sprinkle on top of cake.
I use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heath bars break easier if frozen.

title: holiday wassail
directions: Press cloves into orange slices.
Combine all and heat.
Simmer about 5 minutes and serve.
Makes 5 1/2-quarts, about 30 (6 ounce) servings.

title: chocolate chocolate cake
directions: Spread oil in pan.
Mix all other ingredients; pour into oiled pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Cut butter on top all around.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Remove tips from squash.
Put squash, red peppers, green peppers, onions and salt in a large enamel kettle.
Mix well and let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Put in a large saucepan and add turmeric, curry powder, celery salt, pepper, cornstarch, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring constantly to keep from sticking.
Pack in pint jars and seal.
If desired, one or two hot peppers can be added.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie pan 2/3 full with peeled, sliced apples.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon, mixed.
Combine butter, 1 cup sugar, flour, egg, nuts and salt.
Pour over apples.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into deep, hot oil at 375°, frying only a few at a time, until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Yields about 2 dozen hush puppies.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and molasses.
Mix dry ingredients into creamed mixture. Chill at least 1 hour.
Form into balls and roll in additional sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These should be soft to the touch.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and save one can coconut and about 2 dozen cherries to decorate top.
This looks really nice in a cut glass bowl for the holidays.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Top with another 1/2 cup of Velveeta cheese, diced.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.
Great the next day reheated.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, pecans and coconut in saucepan. Heat until butter and sugar are melted.
Stir.
Spread in bottom of hot pie shell.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and seasonings. Stir in onions, spinach, water chestnuts and pepper.
Cover; refrigerate to blend flavors.
Serve with crisp vegetable dippers, assorted crackers or bread.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: swiss eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover bottom of a shallow greased casserole with 1 cup grated cheese.
Make 6 depressions in cheese. Slide an egg into each depression.
Sprinkle with cream or milk, salt, pepper and parsley.
Top with 1/2 to 1 cup additional grated cheese.
Bake 25 minutes or until eggs are firm but not hard. Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Crush croutons and cover bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Put sausage on top of croutons.
Cover sausage with cheese. Mix eggs and milk and pour over top of cheese.
Let set overnight. Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into chunks.
Melt butter and put in a casserole dish.
Mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper in large bowl. Add potatoes and stir.
Pour into casserole and add milk.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Stir at 1/2 hour.
Do not cover during baking.

title: oreo banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding by directions.
Let set a few minutes.
Add 1/2 bowl Cool Whip.
In large deep bowl, slice a layer of bananas. Arrange cookies over bananas.
Repeat.
Cover with Cool Whip. Chill before serving.

title: mrs. e. leo andrews valentine icebox cake
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken. Fold in the marshmallows, strawberries and whipped cream. Pour mixture over sliced or broken up angel food cake. Leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: herb vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except the oils.
Shake well. Add the oils and shake.
Great over vegetables, pasta, salads, greens, etc.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies(no sugar)
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine wet ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to wet and stir thoroughly (do not beat).
Bake on nonstick pans for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add sugar and blend.
In another bowl, combine fruits and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and combine with cream cheese mixture.

title: takahashi's teriyaki sauce
directions: Stir
dry
ingredients
together, then add liquid.
You should have a
sweet, salty taste.
This is good on beef, pork and chicken.

title: pizza horns
directions: Thaw
frozen
bread in refrigerator overnight or at room temperature 2 to 3 hours.
On lightly floured surface, roll out each loaf into a
circle,
about
10 inches diameter.
Cut each circle into 8 triangles
or wedges.
Spread with sauce to which oregano and garlic powder
are added.
Leave 1/4-inch margin on each side.
Sprinkle
with
cheese, green pepper and pepperoni. Roll up triangle beginning
from
wide end.
Curve ends to form crescents.
Place on
lightly
oiled baking sheets.
Brush with egg white and garnish
with
oregano
and cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: leinbach's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together salad oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Combine with egg mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage in heavy pan with oil 15 minutes on medium heat on stove top; cabbage will be steamed down.
Add milk, flour and cornmeal.
Cover and cook on low heat 20 minutes or until thick. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the Jell-O, sugar and boiling water.
Mix the cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water.
Combine ingredients and bring to a boil until thick and clear.
Cool, then refrigerate until cold. Combine with fresh strawberries.
Put in baked and cooled shell. Serve with whipped cream.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ida's sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Set aside.
Cream until fluffy, oleo and sugars.
Add slightly beaten egg and vanilla and mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.

title: mint chocolate chip torte
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cookie crumbs and margarine; reserve 1/4 cup crumbs.
Press remaining crumbs in bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of 9-inch springform pan.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Place ice-cream in large bowl; gently fold whipped cream into ice-cream. Spoon mixture into crust lined pan.
Sprinkle with reserve crumbs. Cover and freeze for 5 hours or overnight.

title: five-flavors cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Shape into balls on cookie sheet.
Dip a fork or glass in sugar and flatten each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: florentine puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients except patty shells.
Press each quarter shell into small ungreased tart pans (1 1/2-inches in diameter, 24 per pan).
Fill shells and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: frozen lemon dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat milk until fluffy. Add sugar and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour over graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mushrooms, in a skillet. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for ten minutes.
Stir in mushrooms and simmer for five minutes.
Let cool.
Cover and chill several hours.
Drain before serving, removing garlic and bay leaf.

title: breakfast bread pudding
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, beat eggs lightly.
Add artificial sweetener, milk, bread and vanilla.
Mix well.
Cook on Medium-high power in microwave.
Let set 5 minutes.
If not set, cook 2 to 3 minutes longer at Medium power.
Makes 2 servings.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Beat the ingredients with eggbeaters until soft enough to put into cookie press.
Press the dough into long strips on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375°, depending on your oven. Leave in the oven 8 minutes.
If slightly tan at edges, turn the pan for just a few minutes.
When other side turns tan at edges, take out of oven.
When still hot, cut the strips in smaller pieces, the length you prefer.
Cool.
When cold, put in box with tight cover.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together and add vanilla.
Add flour and work into mixture until blended.
Add potato chips and nuts and mix thoroughly.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with hand.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sieved powdered sugar while slightly warm.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: reba's lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add lemon juice and stir well. Refrigerate until thickened.
Beat until light and creamy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Saute zucchini and onions in small amount of butter. Combine soup and sour cream; add the grated carrots, zucchini and onions and mix well. Melt 1 stick butter and mix quickly with stuffing mix; layer 1/2 mixture in bottom of casserole, then layer zucchini mixture, next top with remaining stuffing mixture. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes. Makes 4-6 servings.

title: artichoke casserole(easy and delicious)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread 1 pound of the dough on a large Teflon cookie sheet.
Use the entire length of the sheet.
Spread it to about 7 inches in width.

title: spam picnic casserole
directions: Cook Creamettes according to directions on package.
Combine soup, milk, onion and green peppers.
Place over low heat; add black pepper.
Also, add cheese, stirring occasionally, until melted.
Drain Creamettes and mix with the cheese sauce.
Pour half mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with 6 slices of Spam.
Add balance of mixture with 6 more slices of Spam on top. When ready to serve, put in oven at 325° and bake 30 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown and crumble sausage (use 1 tablespoon oil if browning turkey sausage).
Add one chopped medium
onion and one chopped bell pepper and saute until softened.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer on top of stove for 20 to 30 minutes until rice is cooked through.
Serves 6 to 8.
May be frozen and takes well to reheating in the microwave.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Brown hamburg and sausage.
Add spices to meat while cooking. After meat is browned, add cheese until melted.
Put cut English muffins on cookie sheet.
Top with meat mixture. Put under broiler until bubbly.

title: georgia peanut cookies
directions: Cream the butter with sugar and peanut butter; add vanilla and egg, beating until fluffy.
Stir in baking soda and salt.
Blend in flour.
Mix until a stiff dough forms.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork crosswise to flatten.
Sprinkle with peanuts, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: creamy cocoa frosting
directions: Sift together cocoa and sugar.
Add butter and milk.
Stir until well blended.

title: black forest trifle
directions: Take strawberry jello and dilute with water. Add lemon juice. Let cool a little. Pour over layers in bowl. Set aside for several hours or overnight in a cool place. Don't panic if bananas turn a little dark. When mixture is set, fix vanilla custard (I use several packages of instant vanilla pudding) and cover layers about 1-inch. Cover all layers with whipped cream (I use about 3 1/2 pints of whipping cream). Let set for about 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: all american clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon in pan until crisp.
Remove from pan and break into 1-inch pieces.
Brown onion in bacon fat.
Add clam juice and potatoes.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes until potatoes are done.
Blend in bacon pieces and minced clams the other ingredients.
Heat but do not boil.
Bacon may be used as garnish.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dilute apple juice as directed.
Add orange juice; stir well. Add pineapple juice; stir well.
Add Hawaiian Punch;
mix well.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cook 3 minutes the first 3 ingredients.
Combine oatmeal, orange rind and chopped nuts.
Add all to hot ingredients with 1 cup small marshmallows.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and chill in refrigerator.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of microwave dish.
Spread chili over top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Microwave on High power for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: magic blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of cake pan. Mix milk, sugar, flour and baking powder and pour over butter.
Pour berries over batter. Sprinkle sugar over top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Berries will sink and batter will rise to cover them.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and whip.
Add mayonnaise, catsup, onion, lemon juice and seasoned salt; mix well.
Add chopped shrimp. Serve with tortilla corn chips.

title: grilled butterflied leg of lamb
directions: Ask your butcher to butterfly the meat.
("Butterfly" - remove the bone and open out flat.
It is approximately 1 to 2-inches in thickness).
