Rinse the meat thoroughly with cold water and pat dry with paper towel.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour, shortening, sugar and yeast (dissolved) with a pastry blender or fork.
Slowly add buttermilk.
Knead well.
Cut out biscuits and bake 10 to 20 minutes at 400° (depends on oven). Do not let biscuits rise.
Makes tall, moist biscuits.
This is the only recipe I ever use.
Serve with fried chicken, sausage gravy or just jelly and honey.
A big family favorite.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Pat into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over baked layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. While warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Grated cheese can be sprinkled on top for variation.

title: fig-lemon conserve
directions: Mix figs and sugar in a heavy saucepan.
Cook on low for 15 minutes.
Add gelatin; mix well.
Seal in hot jars.

title: pizza tofu extraordinnaire
directions: Blend to smooth the tofu, garlic, onion, olive oil, salt, cayenne pepper, flax seed and water.

title: new year's cake(vasilopeta keik)
directions: Separate egg yolks and egg whites.
Beat egg whites and set aside.
Beat egg yolks and set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter and slowly add sugar; continue beating until creamy.
Slowly beat in egg yolks and flour with baking powder alternating with milk.
Lastly, add beaten egg whites and baking soda, which has been dissolved in lemon juice.

title: seafood dip
directions: Melt butter and soup in medium saucepan.
Add cream cheese, stirring often.
Drain seafood, reserving liquid.
Add seafood to mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Remove from stove.
Add reserved liquid.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Chill. Then add ginger ale just before serving.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix together the sour cream, soup, milk, onions, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over Tater Tots.
Top with cheese and hamburger.
Sprinkle with the cornflakes (crushed), mixed with the melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tar baby pie
directions: Cut bananas over crusts. Mix prepared Dream Whip, sugar and cream cheese to make the filling. Pour over bananas, spoon blueberry pie filling over the filling. Chill overnight.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix flour, sugar and yeast together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and knead.
Let rise. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat last 3 ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over first 4 ingredients.
Stir thoroughly and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix meal, flour,
soda, salt, eggs, oil and buttermilk. Add onion, peppers and corn;
mix
well.
Bake
at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: great green rice!
directions: Combine rice, broccoli, soup, Cheez Whiz and milk in a buttered casserole dish (2-quart).
Top with buttered bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes (uncovered) at 350°.

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients.
Stir in milk.
When blended, place dough on floured bread board and knead for 2 to 3 minutes. Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Place on greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: apricot delight
directions: Mix the flour, crackers, coconut, brown sugar and baking powder.
Add the melted margarine.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 2/3 of the flour mixture, pressing down.
Pour the apricot pie filling over mixture.
Cover with remaining 1/3 of flour mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix pasta sauce, zucchini and basil. Spread 1/3 of mixture in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish, then top with half the noodles. Mix Ricotta cheese, Parmesan and oregano, then spread over noodles in dish. Spread with 1/3 of the pasta sauce mixture. Top with remaining noodles and sauce mixture. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Let stand 15 minutes. Cut into wedges. Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 3 (8-inch) layers or tube pan.

title: strawberry cake
directions: In bowl, mix as listed the cake mix, Jell-O, oil, water, eggs and strawberries.
Beat according to directions on box.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, at 325°, until layers spring back when touched. When baked and cooled, pour juice over layers.
Put layers on tinfoil to absorb juices.
Spread top with Cool Whip or Dream Whip.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating slowly.
Sift salt, baking powder and flour together.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately, covering nuts with last addition of flour.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 315°.

title: harvest soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Blend flour and milk in a bowl.
Add to soup.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Stir in parsley and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Cook until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grilled asparagus
directions: Put asparagus on foil with butter and salt and pepper.	Grill on medium for about 10 minutes.
Mix 1 cup sour cream, 2 Tbsp. of red wine vinegar, 1/4 cup dijon mustard, pinch of red pepper, 2 teaspoons of sugar and microwave for 1 1/2 minutes then pour over.

title: spiced mandarin mold
directions: Place orange liquid and water in pan with cloves and cinnamon and bring to a boil.
Remove cloves and cinnamon.
Add oranges and pecans.
Put into bowl, pan or mold and chill until jelled.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Cover bottom of rectangular pan with graham crackers.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Then mix with Cool Whip; add another layer of graham crackers.
Cover with chocolate icing.

title: cranberry baked chicken
directions: Saute onions and garlic in margarine in a heavy saucepan until onions are tender.
Combine cranberry and French dressing in a blender.
Place chicken in a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until sauce is bubbling.
Serves 12.

title: shrimp pilau
directions: Chip up and fry meat.
Chop pepper and onion and add to fried meat and grease.
Cook until light brown. Slice up sausage and cook a few minutes longer.
Add tomato juice, hot sauce, salt, pepper and sugar. Bring to simmer. Add cold water.
Pour in rice and cook until about 3/4 cooked or tender, then add raw shrimp that have been prepared.
Keep stirring several times all the way through cooking.

title: baked lemon pudding
directions: Sift together the sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat 3 egg whites in a separate bowl until stiff.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon at a time.
Set aside.
In another bowl, without washing the beaters, beat yolks until light.
Add the lemon rind and juice, melted butter and milk.
Stir into the flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in beaten egg whites. Pour into a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water 1/2-inch deep.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Set aside. Mix flour, oatmeal, salt, soda and powder. Slowly mix dry mixture into creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts. Roll into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 9 dozen.

title: mandarin salad (orange goop)
directions: Mix Cool Whip, orange juice concentrate and condensed milk. Fold in oranges.
Sprinkle with crackers and chill.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine cider with brown sugar, spices and salt in a saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a boil. Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot with lemon slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked chicken croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs, in order given.
Form into 4 croquettes.
Roll in fine crumbs.
Place on brown paper, clipped to cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes. Serve with gravy.

title: spinach with sour cream
directions: If spinach is fresh or frozen, cook then drain.
Chop spinach in mixing bowl and add all other ingredients.
Bake in greased (lightly) casserole at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Do not overcook.
It will separate.

title: cheese balls
directions: *Chopped or can be put in blender.

title: cream taco
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Put in 4-quart saucepan. Cook chili according to directions on package.
Canned chili does not taste as well as brick chili, but will do if you can't find brick chili.
Add to the ground beef.
Mix Velveeta with the whipping cream and add Ro-Tel.
Add this cheese mixture to the meat mixture.
Add 2 cans chili hot beans.
Simmer for 30 minutes. To serve, crunch up chips on plates, spoon meat mixture over chips and top with tossed salad.

title: mexican meat
directions: Cook ingredients in a large saucepan on medium high, stirring frequently for 15 to 30 minutes, then simmer for 30 to 60 minutes. Serve on hot dog rolls. Some like to place a slice of cheese in roll, then put meat over it. Hot dogs are also good with this.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in shallow baking dish.

title: chicken pasta primavera
directions: Slice chicken into thin strips.
Saute over medium-high heat with 1 tablespoon of oil; add green onions and garlic.
Saute for 1 minute.
Heat remaining oil in skillet; add zucchini and carrots and saute 2 minutes.
Stir in broth, wine, parsley, oregano and pepper.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve over pasta; sprinkle with cheese.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: granny bonniwell's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar very well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt at least twice. Add flour alternately with milk to egg mixture.
Beat well; add extract.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding cream cheese last.
Mix well. Let sit.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Let sit in refrigerator for 4 hours before serving.

title: texas cheese
directions: Mix together; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until set in center.

title: california dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown ground beef and drain; add all other ingredients together.
Add 1 teaspoon Louisiana hot sauce, 2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce and salt to taste.
Simmer on low for 2 hours.
Add more water, if needed.

title: overnight sandwiches
directions: Place 6 slices of bread in a buttered pan.
Spread the cheese over the bread.
Add a layer of chicken.
Top with remaining bread slices, butter sided down.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over the bread.
Cover tightly and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: spicy cheese boat
directions: Cut a hole in bread and remove enough bread to make a boat. Mix all ingredients together. Put into bread. Bake for 1 hour. Use big Scoop Fritos to serve.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add more sour cream if desired for consistency.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Place beef in Dutch oven.
Combine all ingredients, cover and bake for 5 hours in 350°
oven.
Shred beef with fork.
Yields 24 servings.
Serve on onion buns.
I serve this with a vegetable salad.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, and milk in a heavy 2 1/2 quart saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 238. Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts, and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 X 9 inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cinnamon chocolate nut waffles
directions: Beat egg white in a small bowl until stiff and set aside.
Mix together dry ingredients and set aside.
Combine egg yolk, milk and butter.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing until just blended. Add nuts and fold in with beaten egg white until just mixed.
Do not overbeat batter.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel carrots and slice penny size.
Cook in salted water until just tender, uncovered.
Drain.
Mix well tomato soup, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salad oil and mustard.
Add to other ingredients and mix easy.
Let marinate 12 to 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.
Keeps in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks, covered well.

title: goulash
directions: Cook onion, mushrooms, margarine, green pepper, pepper, salt and garlic salt in frying pan.
Add hamburger; cook until done. Add tomato sauce, sugar and grated cheese.
Simmer together, then add cooked macaroni.

title: susie's eggs
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs until fluffy and add mustard, salt and milk.
Beat.
Line pan with 4 slices of bread. Layer 1/2 grated cheese and 1/2 egg mixture on top of bread. Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: peanut butter play doh
directions: Knead together.
Let children make shapes with cookie cutter or use their imaginations.
Guaranteed to occupy children at least 30 minutes!

title: chocolate mint bars
directions: First Layer:
Mix together sugar, 1/2 cup butter, eggs, flour, salt, chocolate
syrup,
vanilla and nuts (if desired). Put into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: sugar-free banana milkshake
directions: Fully freeze the banana. Thoroughly puree in a blender or food processor all ingredients. Serve immediately. Makes 1 shake.

title: depression lima bean casserole
directions: Microwave directions:
Place drained lima beans in a 4-quart, microwave-safe casserole.
Add 4 cups of water and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Cover; cook on High 14 to 18 minutes.
Stir; cook on Medium-low for 40 to 45 minutes.
Drain and reserve liquid.

title: cucumber with dill and sour cream
directions: Salt cucumbers and let stand.
Drain off excess water from cucumbers.
After cucumbers are completely drained, add dill, sour cream, mayonnaise, and black pepper.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: beef-cabbage soup
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add the next 9 ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and beans; bring to rolling boil.
Add cabbage; cook for 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix box of cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Mix the caramels with the evaporated milk and the margarine.
Melt these 3 ingredients over low heat.
Pour mixture over baked cake and sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramel mixture.
Pour rest of cake mixture over this and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Frost with chocolate cream frosting, if desired.

title: french-fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions and cut into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings.
Dip onion rings in milk and then in seasoned flour.
Fry a few at a time until lightly browned in deep Crisco heated to 365°. Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve while hot!
Yields 4 servings.

title: grandma's silk pie
directions: Melt chocolate over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine butter and sugar in a large bowl; beat until light and fluffy (about 4 minutes).
Add melted chocolate and water; beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm (2 hours).

title: pineapple cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Chill.

title: calabacita
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, remove and drain.
Season beef with salt, pepper and garlic.
Saute with onion in bacon drippings.
Add catsup, tomatoes (mashed) and zucchini.
Cover and cook until tender.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and top with crumbled bacon. Serves 6.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop from a large tablespoon into shortening.
Fry approximately 1 - 2 minutes on each side until golden brown.

title: filled cookies (cut outs)
directions: Cream together, lard and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll out on well floured surface, cut.
Better if dough sets awhile.
Fill with desired filling.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: easy spiced tea
directions: Steep tea and spices 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add sugar and juices.
Serve hot.

title: olive tuna dip
directions: Whip cream cheese with enough milk to make a thick, smooth consistency.
Add tuna fish, olives and seasonings.
Serve with chips, crackers or use as a filling for celery sticks.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Simmer green pepper in water until nearly tender; drain. Combine milk with mayonnaise; add pimento, green pepper, mushrooms, water chestnuts, chicken and top with onion rings. Cover and bake 15 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 5 minutes longer, to crisp onion rings.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: granola
directions: Mix together dry ingredients in large roasting pan.
Add oil, honey and molasses; mix well.
Bake at 250° and stir every 15 minutes for an hour or until golden brown.
Cool and add coconut and raisins.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients, except pie crust.
Pour into crust. Chill well before serving.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Melt margarine in broiler pan.
Mix uncooked rice, onion and beef consomme; add to broiler pan.
Place pork chops on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Combine and melt together.
Enjoy with tortilla chips.

title: shrimp kabobs
directions: Marinate in teriyaki sauce for 10 to 15 minutes.
Thread onto 12 skewers and broil or grill for 8 to 10 minutes, turning often. Serve with seasoned or white rice.

title: christmas rice
directions: Mix all together in casserole dish.
Bake one hour in oven at 350°.
Stir about 3 times during cooking.

title: 7-up bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar and butter together; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well. Add flour, a cup at a time, and mix well after each cup.
Add lemon extract and 7-Up; mix well.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Put on rack to cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut up fruits in squares (enough for the amount you need). In a large 4-quart bowl, mix instant pudding, using buttermilk instead of milk; mix until stiff. Add 1 box whip cream; pour over fruits.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Slice butter into small pieces and stir into mixture.
Add egg and almond extract. Mix well.
Spoon dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes and enjoy!

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine the last 3 and spread over top of layers.
Cover tightly and let set for several hours before serving.
Toss before serving.

title: taco noodle casserole
directions: Cook ground beef according to directions on taco seasoning. Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Mix ground beef mixture, noodles and tomato sauce together.
Spread in a casserole dish and cover with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° until the cheese is melted.

title: chilies and rice casserole
directions: Season rice with salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, 1 teaspoon salt and chilies.

title: egg and cheese bake
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Grate or chop the cheese. Add cheese to butter and stir well. Cut crust from the bread and cube. Butter a large 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 small pans.
In a large bowl, mix bread, cheese, meat and butter.
Pour into pan(s).
Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour egg mixture into pan. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Burn 1/2 cup sugar to a deep brown.
Add water.
Let dissolve. Then add to other mixture and bake in hot oven.
Use caramel icing.

title: gillie's cheesy egg grits
directions: Stir grits into boiling water.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in egg(s).
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When 1 minute left to cook, stir in cheese.
Serve hot topped with pat of butter or margarine and toast on side.
Makes 1 serving. Multiply accordingly.

title: mamaw's shrimp cocktail
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill thoroughly before serving.
If the shrimp are medium or larger, they should be cut up some.
Note that this is already mixed when served, and not used with the shrimp dipped into the sauce.
I once found some of this in the fridge and got sick gorging on it before I got caught.
This is my mother's recipe.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; chop 3/4 of the chipped beef and green onions (small part of the green).
Mix all the rest of ingredients together and refrigerate until chilled.
Roll into 1 large ball or 2 to 3 smaller ones, then roll again in saved chipped beef to coat.
Refrigerate again.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, sugar and vinegar together in pot; bring to boil. Remove from heat for 5 minutes.
Add bottle of pectin.
Do not substitute.
Pour in 1/2-pint jars; seal.
Yield:
4 pints.

title: brussel sprouts and ham
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts to directions on box.
Melt margarine; add chestnuts and ham.
Add to Brussels sprouts.

title: broccoli salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with Poppy Seed Dressing.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to directions on the box. In a 13 x 9 pan, bake. Cool 20 or 30 minutes. Poke holes in the cake with a fork. In mixing bowl, mix together the cream of coconut and condensed milk. At this time, the cake can be refrigerated or frozen for up to 1 month. Thaw overnight in the fridge. Top with Cool Whip.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, macaroni, cheese and milk.
Pour into a large buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad 1
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Add bananas and apple. Stir in mayonnaise and then the Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble bread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over toast, then cheese.
Mix in bowl the eggs, half and half, mustard and salt.
Pour this mixture over cheese.
Cover with foil; refrigerate for 8 hours.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: chop chai
directions: Put Chinese noodles in boiling water 15 minutes.
Drain; rinse in cold water and drain again.
Set aside.
Put 1 tablespoon oil in a skillet and when hot, add carrot strips.
Fry until carrots are barely soft.
Remove and set aside.
Add more oil to skillet. When hot, cook onion slices the same way.
Do same with mushrooms and set aside.
Wash celery and fry.
Add strips of steak, green onion slivers and minced garlic.
Fry.
Combine ingredients. Season with soy sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pork and beef barbecue
directions: Season meats with salt and pepper.
Place in crock-pot.
Add celery and onion.
Cook in meats' own juices for 8 hours or all day.
Transfer contents of pot to large bowl, straining pan juices. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chili green beans
directions: Cook beans covered about 10 minutes with onion, salad oil, water and salt.
Last minute spoon 1/4 c. chili sauce over and then serve.

title: apple harvest squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla. Mix in salt, flour and coconut and stir well.
Reserve 3/4 cup for topping.
Spread the rest in a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Spread apricot preserves over mixture.
Sprinkle nuts over preserves. Crumble reserved 3/4 cup dough over top.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into 24 bars.

title: scalloped creamed corn
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: alphabet salad
directions: Drain and save the juice from the fruit.

title: never fail icebox rolls
directions: Put milk in 2-quart saucepan; add sugar.
Add shortening. Scald milk (do not boil) with sugar and shortening added; remove from heat.
Add salt.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add yeast cakes and stir until dissolved.
Beat in flour gradually, then toss on floured breadboard; knead lightly.
Place back in pan and let rise until doubled, approximately 2 hours.
Take out of pan and knead again.
Roll dough and make into rolls.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Spoon liquid shortening or melted butter on tops of rolls.
Cover and let rise in warm place approximately 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in size.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a bowl, mix bread, cream, water and all other ingredients, mixing well. Place in an ungreased 13-inch pan. Place in a preheated oven at 300° for 35 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini-hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to hamburger.
Place in buttered, 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: okra bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 7 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch square pan.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together oil and sugar; beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to first ingredients and mix well.
Then add apples and pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours in tube cake pan.

title: baked beans(abington grange supper)
directions: Pick over the beans and soak them overnight in cold water.
In the morning, parboil the beans until the skins crack when blown upon.
If an onion is used, cut in quarters and put in bottom of bean pot.
Add the parboiled beans.
Cut through the rind of the salt pork to a depth of 1/2-inch.
Place the pork on top of the beans; mix the sugar, molasses, mustard, pepper and salt with 1 pint boiling water.
Pour this over the beans and pork.
If necessary, add more boiling water to cover.
Bake at 300° for 5 or 6 hours, adding more boiling water as the beans cook.

title: cranberry surprise salad
directions: Chop cranberries;
add	sugar and let stand 10 minutes. Mix gelatine with
sugar
and
salt;
add
to

hot water until dissolved.	Add lemon juice, rind and mayo to gelatine mixture and blend with beater.	Quick chill this mixture in refrigerator tray, 15 minutes or until firm, 1 inch from edge, but soft in center. Then
beat	until
fluffy.	Fold in cranberry mixture, pineapple and
nuts.	Pour
into
1 quart mold and chill until firm.	Unmold on lettuce.
Top with mayo.
Serves 6.

title: chicken supreme
directions: In medium bowl, blend 2 tablespoons melted butter and cream cheese until smooth. Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onions. Mix well. Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations together.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture on rectangle. Fold corners together and twist.
Brush with butter. Sprinkle with croutons. Cook on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Serves 2 to 4.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Put beans, water, bacon, salt and pepper in a large boiler. Cook until beans are just about done with a good bit of juice left in pot. Stir in rice and bring to a boil.
Cover and turn down to simmer and let cook about 30 minutes.

title: special peach cocktail
directions: Add enough peeled peaches to absorb most of the juice.
Bag and freeze.
Chop bananas in for fruit cocktail.
Add 7-Up for slush.
Pour 2 cups boiling water into 6 ounces apricot jello; add 1 bag mixture.

title: dijon-lemon marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Use to marinate fish or poultry before cooking.
Baste with remaining marinade while cooking (7 calories per cup).
Good for diabetic, high blood pressure or watching calories.

title: gypsy beans
directions: In a stock pot, bring water to a boil.
Add the tomato paste, paprika, Tabasco, salt, black pepper and red and green bell peppers.
Drain the olives and add to the soup.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Add the bag of beans.
Cover with lid on medium heat. Cook for 45 minutes to an hour.
Add 1/2 cup water if needed. Serves 6.

title: corn royale
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, saute celery and onion in buttermilk until crisply tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat through. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix with soups.
Remove from heat and add sour cream and chicken.	Toss with spaghetti and top with grated Parmesan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs with mixer, then add other ingredients, except nuts. Then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar and vanilla in bowl and mix well with mixer.
Pour into can; add condensed milk and stir well.
Add enough milk to reach fill line on freezer can and stir.

title: winter warmer casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and vegetables until meat is browned.
Drain off any grease in pan.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and simmer until well blended.
Sprinkle cheese over top and simmer until cheese melts.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend in blender 2 minutes. Keep refrigerated.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Mix together and cook.
Will thicken as it cools.

title: lemon oat bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
In small bowl, stir together condensed milk and lemon juice until blended (add lemon rind). Set mixture aside.
In medium bowl, beat together butter and brown sugar.
Stir together baking powder and oats; add to lemon mixture, stirring until well blended.
Mixture will be crumbly. Spread half the mixture in pan, patting down firm.
Spread lemon mixture over top; sprinkle with rest of oat mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes (until brown around the edges).
Cool on rack 15 minutes.
Chill before cutting into bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ruby's corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and chow.

title: wassail
directions: In cheesecloth bag, put 1 tablespoon whole cloves and 1 tablespoon whole allspice. Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes (I use crock-pot on low). Remove spice bag. Keep warm in crock-pot. Serve with cinnamon stick in cup for festive look.

title: curried split-pea soup
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat peas, remaining ingredients and 5 cups water to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 50 minutes or until peas are tender.
This is about 180 calories per serving and very tasty.

title: crunchy blueberry muffin recipe
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, whip the egg substitute until foamy.
Add and blend the creamer and oil. Add flour mixture and mix until just blended.
Fold in blueberries and cereal.
Pour into lined muffin cups to 2/3 full. Bake in preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar and let sit.
Add oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add together; pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: Cook and drain potatoes. Add chopped eggs, onion, celery and pickles. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: albert's game hens
directions: Mix
soy,
sherry,
ginger and green onions in a baking dish. Marinate
quartered game hens at least 6 hours, turning occasionally.
In
a
skillet of medium hot oil, fry game hens until golden brown (about 20 minutes).
Remove game hen pieces and drain.
Place in a dish and brush with honey.

title: milk shakes
directions: Mix the milk and ice cream in a bowl.
Beat with spoon or use a blender or mixer.
Add fruit and serve.

title: fudge icing
directions: Warm slightly the butter, but don't melt it.
Cream butter with confectioners sugar.
When thoroughly blended, beat in egg, melted bitter chocolate and vanilla.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Sift together the flour and cocoa. Dissolve the baking soda in 1 c. hot water.

title: toffee crunch
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and 3/4 cup of the pecans in a heavy saucepan.

Cook over medium flame, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches hard crack stage (syrup separates into threads that are hard and brittle) or 300° on candy thermometer. Pour onto lightly buttered baking sheet.
Immediately place chocolate pieces on top of toffee and spread until melted. Lightly press remaining 1 cup pecans into chocolate.
Cool completely; break in pieces.
Makes 1 pound.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, place first four ingredients; stir.
Add warm water; stir.
Allow mixture to set 5 minutes; stir.
Add 4 of the 6 cups of flour to make stiff dough.
On floured board, knead in remainder of flour until lumps are gone and dough has elasticity.
Place dough back into mixing bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until dough has doubled in size.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix the flour, baking soda and salt together; set aside. Cream together the oleo, sugars, vanilla and pudding.
Beat in the eggs.
Gradually add the flour mixture.
Stir in the chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with sliced apples.
Cover with above ingredients, mixed together.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: french bread
directions: Mix warm water, yeast, salt and sugar.
Let stand 5 to 6 minutes.
Add 5 cups flour and beat well.
Add remaining flour until you can handle the dough without it being sticky.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Put in bowl and let stand dough rise until double in size.
Remove from bowl and cut into four sections.
Shape into narrow loaves (2 loaves to a cookie sheet) or into round mounds. Beat egg whites and water.
Brush top of loaves and let stand for 1 hour.
Makes three slits on top of each loaf.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes. Brush once during cooking process with the egg white mixture.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased tube pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl.
In small bowl whisk together oil, vinegar, mustard, jalapeno, salt and pepper. Pour over pea mixture and serve immediately.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn and put into clean paper grocery bag.
In glass bowl, mix margarine, Karo and brown sugar.
Microwave on High until mixture boils, about 2 minutes.
Continue cooking an additional 2 minutes on High.
Add baking soda; stir well.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Shake well.
Fold top of bag to close it and place bag in microwave.
Cook in bag for an additional 4 1/2 minutes on High, stopping microwave every minute to shake bag vigorously.
Pour into large bowl to cool.
Stir popcorn in bowl for several minutes or until it is cool enough that it won't stick together.
Cool completely before storing in airtight container.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Melt oleo and brown sugar in bottom of 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Arrange pineapple and cherries in oleo and brown sugar.

title: ham and cheese souffle
directions: Layer bread, ham and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle flour over the mixture.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard together; pour over mixture in pan.
Cover.
Chill overnight or at least 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great for breakfast.

title: calico beans
directions: Partially drain beans and mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or simmer in crock-pot for several hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Spread 4 cups potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients, 3/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Pour half over potatoes.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer.
You can add 2 cups shredded cheese the last 15 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Mix cocoa and boiling water to dissolve cocoa.
Add to first mixture.
Mix in order given.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mexican cornbread - african american style
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck, onions and salt in a skillet.
In large cooker, heat tomato juice, beans and chili powder.
Pour meat and onions in cooker and slow cook 45 minutes.
Let cool about 2 hours before serving.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: savory boiled mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
In a large saucepan, prepare broth by mixing water with the 4 packets mix.
Cut green pepper into moderately large pieces and drop into broth.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Cook over medium heat until mushrooms are tender. Thicken broth with cornstarch mixed with a small amount of cold water.
Good as a side dish with beef.
tags: packets individual serving size beef broth mix

title: shrimp dip
directions: Grind or finely chop shrimp.
Make sure no peelings or shells are left.
Add shrimp along with spices, lemon juice and Worcestershire to already softened cream cheese.
Chill.
Serve with a variety of chips and crackers.
Great for parties.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine with chocolate squares.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and add pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: whop biscuits
directions: Whop one can on the side of the counter. Place in pan and bake according to directions on can.

title: hearts n' caps(to steal his heart, serve with roast or grilled meat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange artichoke hearts in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of the Parmesan cheese.
Saute mushrooms in butter in medium skillet until tender. Add cream.
Cook over low heat until most of cream is absorbed. Stir occasionally.
Pour mushroom mixture over artichokes and sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Mix in bowl until creamy.
Keeps for 2 weeks in refrigerator. Rewhip before using.
Makes 3 cups.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry hamburger until brown. Drain fat. Combine all other ingredients together in saucepan and heat thoroughly. Put over fried hamburger and serve on bun.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add vinegar and water.
Mix together. Cook, stirring constantly, until beets are heated.
Add butter and stir.

title: old fashioned sand tarts
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Roll into walnut size balls and press down with end of small glass or disc from cookie press dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top, and chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed minute steak
directions: Mix honey and soy sauce. Set aside. Combine hot water and butter. Stir in Stove Top. Spoon 1/2 cup stuffing on each steak. Roll steak and secure with picks.
Put into baking dish.
Spoon honey mixture on top. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 6 ingredients; freeze.
When ready to serve, stir to a mush.
Add Sprite and 7-Up.
Serve.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Flour the chicken. Brown the chicken in a large pot in the oil.
Remove and keep warm.

In the same pan, lightly brown the onion, garlic, mushrooms and parsley. Return the chicken to the pot and add the tomato paste, water and remaining spices. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add the wine and simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: golden salad
directions: Mix gelatin, sugar, salt and pineapple juice in small saucepan. Heat over low heat until gelatine is dissolved.
Remove from heat; add other juices.
Chill to unbeaten egg white consistency.
Fold in other ingredients.
Pour into 3-cup mold; chill until firm.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco; add sugar gradually, creaming well.
Add egg yolks, beating well.
Add soda to buttermilk and add alternately with flour to sugar mixture and beat slowly.
Add coconut and nuts and fold in beaten egg whites.
Makes 3 layers. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: biscuit dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening with 2 knives, a fork or pastry blender.
Add milk, using more if necessary to make a soft dough.
Pat out to 1/2-inch thick and cut into 1-inch squares.
Drop into boiling chicken or beef stock.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cherry delight pie
directions: Fold whipping cream into condensed milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with cherry pie filling. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: barbecue roast beef or pork
directions: Brown onions in skillet; then add vinegar, brown sugar, mustard, ketchup, water, Worcestershire sauce and celery.
Simmer together for about 20 minutes.
Add cooked cubes of meat to the sauce.
Simmer for another 20 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: In large bowl, melt chips, peanut butter and margarine together in microwave.
Add Chex; thoroughly mix together.
In large grocery sack, add Chex and powdered sugar.
Shake until it is all covered.
You may need to add more powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: spinach balls
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir ingredients together except stuffing.
Add stuffing.
Cover and stand for 20 minutes.
Use a teaspoon for forming balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 30 to 50 balls.

title: zucchini - cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, add rice and onion to a rapid boil.
Cover tightly; boil gently 20 minutes.

title: kahlua liqueur
directions: You will also need 1/2 gallon sterilized glass jug with lid.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a free boil. Remove immediately from heat. Mix in peanut butter in 9 x 13 pan. Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips. Spread icing over first mixture. Cut into bars to serve.

title: savory green beans with croutons
directions: Cook beans 7 minutes until just tender.
Place in colander and run cold water through them.
Saute croutons in butter and add seasonings and beans.
Mix and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: caramel corn
directions: Stir sugar over low heat until melted and golden brown.
Stir in carefully water and brown sugar. Cook to 238° or until a little dropped into cold water forms a soft ball.
Pour over popped corn. Mix gently to coat well.
Spread out on wax paper to cool so pieces separate.
Can add any kind of nut if desired.

title: grandma dorr's white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warmed milk.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° until done.
Makes 6 to 8 loaves.

title: basic yellow cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla. Cream well.
Add 1/2 flour and 1/2 milk.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat at high speed after each addition.
Add other 1/2 flour with baking powder and other 1/2 milk.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Bake in three layers at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil,
chocolate
and
sugar together.
Blend in one egg at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, powdered sugar
and	add
to
chocolate mix.
Drop small balls into powdered sugar and roll.
Place 2 inches apart on greased sheet. Bake at
for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake, as chocolate tastes burned.

title: hershey bar chocolate pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and candy bars in milk in double boiler and cool.
Whip cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix 1st four ingredients together and pour sugar over ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Stir before serving.
(Will last for months.)

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to chocolate mixture.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave butter toffee
directions: In a large, microwave-safe bowl, mix sugar, butter, water and corn syrup.
Microwave on High power (100%) 4 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes longer or until mixture thickens and turns golden.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over hot toffee; spread with a spatula before chocolate hardens. Sprinkle with walnuts.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces. Store in airtight container.
Yields about 1 1/4 pounds.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix by hand yams, sugar, flour, butter, beaten eggs, vanilla and milk and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: abe's beef and link sandwich
directions: Cook the beef and sausage.
Soak beef in barbecue sauce.
Dice beef and sausage.
Put on bun.
Sprinkle with Tabasco sauce and serve.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, oleo and sugars.
Add vanilla, eggs, soda and water.
Beat or stir well.
Sift flour and salt; add oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir together until mixed well.
Drop from teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes only; do not overbake.

title: go power candy
directions: Pinch off bits and shape into balls.
Roll in wheat germ.

title: sara's praline sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a large bowl, mix sweet potatoes, sugar, vanilla, eggs, milk and margarine. In a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, place the sweet potato mixture.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, add lime juice, condensed milk, and lime rind; mix well.
Pour into pie shell and freeze.
Remove from freezer and spread with whipped cream.
Let sit five minutes before serving.

title: john's red sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Varying amount of horseradish will determine bite of red sauce.

title: dirt
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Whip together pudding and milk.
Mix all this together.
Mix all of this with Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form into ball. Sprinkle parsley flakes on ball and refrigerate.

title: hidden valley pretzels
directions: Mix well all above and pour over pretzels.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix instant pudding and milk.
Add whipped topping.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Spread with 1/2 of the pudding.
Add another layer of whole graham crackers.
Spread the rest of the pudding on.
Add another layer of graham crackers. Frost with chocolate topping.
Refrigerate at least 10 hours before serving.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch strips and season with salt and pepper. Heat oil in skillet; add garlic and ginger.
Saute until garlic is golden.
Add steak slices and brown.
Remove meat from skillet. Add peppers and onions.
Saute until tender.
Place meat back in skillet; add other ingredients and heat.
Serve over rice and/or noodles.

title: louisiana creamy pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla. Cook over low heat to soft ball stage on candy thermometer, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking. Add vanilla. Cool. Beat until thick. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Leave on paper until firm and cool. Yields 20 pieces.

title: corned beef hot sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients very well.
Spread on sandwich buns. Wrap buns in aluminum foil.
Put in oven at 325° until warm.

title: kielbasa boil
directions: Boil kielbasa for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cut up vegetables. Boil until cooked, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain and serve warm.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine tea, sugar and juices (also cherry juice).
Just before serving, add cherries and ginger ale; stir well.
Pour over ice and serve.
Serves about 20.

title: pork chops with dressing
directions: Put chops close together in pan.
Add enough water to cover bottom of pan.
Mix onion, bread crumbs, oil, pepper, salt and 1 well beaten egg with 1/2 cup hot water.
Spread on pork chops. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine all ingredients. Press into pan and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Combine and mix cold water and cornmeal.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling water.
Add cornmeal mixture, stirring constantly, bring to boil.
Partially cover pan.
Cook slowly 7 minutes, stirring often.
Line bottom and sides of casserole dish with mush.
Cook beef and onion until brown.
Stir in flour, salt and chili powder. Add tomatoes, stir in tomato sauce and corn; spoon over mush.
Bake 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter by itself; add sugar.
Beat eggs by itself, well beaten.
Alternate eggs and flour into creamy butter mixture, beating well.
Add flavors.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 322°.

title: mother's seafood salad(servings:  8)
directions: Mix drained seafoods with juice of lemon and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Add macaroni, celery, chopped hard-cooked eggs and mayonnaise to bind.
Can add stuffed olives (sliced, good for added color), pickles (chopped) and egg slices on top.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together.
Mix 1/4 cup cocoa mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: bruschetta with fresh tomatoes and basil
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Wash and cut tomatoes in half. In a bowl, toss the tomatoes with olive oil and basil. Season lightly with salt and pepper. Toast the bread on a sheet pan until crisp. Remove from oven and rub the garlic halves on both sides of the toast. Just before serving, top with tomatoes.

title: quick sugar doughnuts
directions: Remove biscuits from tube.
Flatten a little and push a hole through the center of each.
Fry in oil, heated to 350°, turning once or twice until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve at once.
Makes 10.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Beat eggs and add sugar, oil, vanilla and blend. Stir together the flour mixture and egg mixture. Add the apples and raisins. Stir together, pour into a bundt pan (greased and floured or sugared). Bake at 325 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: mother's vegetable pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add vanilla and egg and beat well. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Fold in raisins.
Fill greased custard cups or muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with the orange sauce below.
Makes 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans. Add pecans and mix well; form into ball. Refrigerate overnight, then roll in chopped nuts to cover outside.

title: golden fudge
directions: Combine in 2 1/2 qt. saucepan brown and white sugars, milk and oleo. Place over medium heat and stir constantly till oleo is melted. Cook over medium heat stirring occasionally till mixture forms soft ball when dropped in cold water, or till temperature reaches 238 degrees on candy thermometer. Remove from heat - stir in butterscotch morsels and marshmallow creme till thoroughly blended. Add nuts, raisins, salt, rum and vanilla. Pour into 2 greased 8 inch square pans and chill. When cold cut into squares.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Bake until done, about 1 hour at 300°.

title: carrot salad
directions: This is a "make ahead" dish.
Mix all ingredients except cucumbers and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
While mix is setting, soak cucumbers in salt water.
Drain cucumbers and add to carrot mixture just before serving.

title: double cooked pork
directions: Boil the whole pork with a little wine, ginger and green onion for 30 minutes.
Remove.
When cool, cut into very thin slices. Cut the green and red peppers into 1-inch squares.
Slice garlic. You may use green garlic if you have. Mix sweet soybean paste with soy sauce, sugar and hot bean paste in a bowl.
Stir-fry pork slices in 3 tablespoons oil for 1 minute.
Add garlic, green and red peppers; stir 1 more minute.
Remove from pan.
Use the remaining oil to stir-fry the sweet soybean paste for 10 seconds. Return pork mixture.
Stir well and serve.

title: never fail noodles
directions: Mix egg yolks, cream and shortening.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Roll out thin on a floured board.
Let dry. Roll up and cut into desired size noodles.
These noodles will keep 6 months in freezer.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour over brown sugar in large bowl; mix well.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour; mix well. Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Pour back into pan and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos.
Mix Jello pudding according to directions. Fold in Cool Whip and half of crushed Oreos.
Pour into dish and cover with remaining Oreos.
Garnish with gummy worms. Refrigerate.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Bring to boil oleo, sugar, water and 1/4 tsp. cinnamon. Save rest of cinnamon for top.
Wrap apples in crust and pour hot ingredients over apples before placing in oven.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes. Delicious!

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil, vanilla, cinnamon and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Fold in apples and chopped nuts.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together flour, butter and powdered sugar until crumbly. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 inch pie pan.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix 3 cups confectioners sugar with 1/4 cup hot water.
Beat in 1 egg and 1/2 cup soft butter until smooth. Add 4 packages Baker's Redi-Blend; beat until creamy. Frosts 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: angel cordial delight cake
directions: Cut cherries in quarters and marshmallows into small pieces. Drain pineapple and combine with cherries and marshmallows.
Let stand about 2 hours.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold milk.
Heat remaining 1/2 cup milk and add to softened gelatin.
Refrigerate until gelatin is partially set.
Add fruit mixture and nuts.
Fold into whipped cream.
Slice cake horizontally into 3 equal sized layers.
Spread fruit filling between cake layers and over the top and sides of the cake.
Chill until mixture is firm.
Refrigerate until served.
May be made 1 day prior to serving.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Combine ingredients, except cheese, stirring lightly.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Based on 12 servings.
Per serving contains 425 calories, 27 g fat, 912 mg sodium and 93 mg cholesterol.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Beat eggs slightly in mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked onions with sour cream
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place the unpeeled onions in a foil-lined shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Warm a heat-proof shallow serving dish.
When onions are tender, remove from oven.
Spear each with a fork, snip or cut off both ends and remove skin.
Place the peeled onions in the warmed dish. Immediately add the butter and sour cream so they will melt from the heat of the onions.
Then add the rest of the ingredients and toss lightly to mix.
Serves 4.

title: sally lunn
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add the beaten eggs. Add the milk alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into a small roasting pan or 2 pie pans and bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: homemade pedialyte - army style
directions: Stir well.
Check with Dr. before using for babies.
Good for adults for replacing body fluids.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add and mix oil and eggs.
Add the strawberries and pecans.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
(I add a drop of red food coloring to make the bread pink.)
Excellent to give as a holiday bread. Stays moist for several days.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix well and serve with crackers. (Or for sandwiches.)

title: stir-fry pepper steak
directions: Put the oil in a skillet, sprinkle in the garlic salt and place over medium heat until hot. Add the steak, green peppers, and mushrooms to skillet. Cook, stirring often, until the meat is cooked as done as you like.

title: cornbread
directions: Grease a heavy pan well.
Sprinkle with meal.
Heat pan slightly.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into heated pan. Bake at 450° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: louisiana crab and crawfish cakes with lemon-fennel remoulade(serves 8)
directions: Saute onions, celery and peppers lightly and allow to cool. Pick through crabmeat to remove all shell pieces.
Fold all ingredients together.
Gently mix so as not to break up crabmeat too much.
Form into cakes (yield 16 pieces) and dredge in fresh bread crumbs.
Saute on both sides until golden brown.
Serve with Lemon-Fennel Remoulade.

title: diet shake 'n bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle over meat (good on chicken livers).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
With 2 tubs of melted margarine, grease pan.
Sprinkle bottom and side of pan with 1/3 cup ground pecans. In medium bowl, sift flour, salt and baking powder.
In large mixing bowl at medium speed, beat 1 cup margarine or butter with sugar until light and fluffy (about 10 minutes, scraping sides and bottom of bowl frequently).
At low speed, add flour mixture; blend thoroughly.
Add eggs and mix at medium speed until just blended. Do not overbeat!
Stir in rum and remaining ground pecans.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake one hour and ten minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cake rest in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and cool completely on rack. Frost with rum glaze; decorate with pecan halves if desired.

title: italian cream cake(excellent)
directions: Cream shortening and oleo; add sugar.
Beat and add egg yolks, then buttermilk and dry ingredients alternately.
Add coconut, vanilla and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Mix sugars, cream and cook to soft ball stage.
After mixture stops bubbling, add margarine, vanilla and pecans.
Beat.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Allow to harden.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and onion juice in a bowl using mixer or rotary beater.
Gradually beat in oil until mixture is thick and smooth.
Fold in poppy seed.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: hot sauce to can
directions: Drop in tomato mixture and simmer 1 hour.
Sterilize jars and seal.
Put rubber gloves on to grind or chop hot peppers.
I make this and it is good on tortillas.

title: christmas candy
directions: Boil to 300° on candy thermometer over medium heat; remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon any flavoring oil to this.
For example: cinnamon, anise; add a few drops any food coloring (coordinate flavoring and color).
Have cookie sheet ready, sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Pour mixture on sheet.
Let it get hard, then break into pieces.

title: fruit pizza
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, chicken soup and sour cream.
Crumble crackers and mix with butter and poppy seeds.
Put 1/2 of cracker mixture in bottom of 8 x 13 pan then spread chicken mixture; top with remaining cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Partially thaw potatoes.
Mix in cheese and rest of ingredients.
Bake in large baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy to make brownies
directions: Blend all ingredients and put in 8 x 8-inch size pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Ice with your favorite frosting.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a jar and shake.
Use to marinate chicken, beef or pork.

title: cream bars
directions: Mix.
Spread on top of other mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Do toothpick test in middle.
Should be golden brown.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling; add potatoes.
Heat to boiling again; reduce heat.
Cover and cook until tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Cook and stir onion in bacon fat until tender.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat, stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.
Crumble bacon into hot mixture, then slice in warm potatoes.
Cook, stirring gently to coat potato slices.

title: mandarin orange meringue gelatin
directions: Tear agar-agar into tiny pieces.
Wash, drain, then soak in 2 cups water for 1 hour.
Cook in a saucepan over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Begin stirring after liquid comes to a simmer.
Add sugar, continue cooking to reduce mixture by half.
Cool.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix together; pour into 2 regular pie shells.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: hearty oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients and add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: microwave fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit saving juices.
Mix pudding and 3 cups of the juices.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Add the fruit and chill.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Melt Velveeta, soup and picante sauce. Serve hot.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat and set aside. Mix mayonnaise, eggs, milk and cornstarch until smooth. Stir in
meat, cheese, pepper and onion. Pour into pie shell. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in "Pammed" sheet cake pan.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and honey together until well combined. Stir in peanut butter; mix well. Fold in thawed whipped topping. Spoon mixture into crust.

title: grandma's bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Scald milk, then add the butter into the milk.
Beat eggs slightly in a bowl.
Add milk mixture, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Put bread and raisins into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour milk mixture over the bread and raisins.
Stir gently.
Place in a pan of hot water in the oven, uncovered.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife 1-inch from the edge comes out clean.
Serves 6.
Tastes good chilled or warm.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients; let stand.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients except butter and crumbs.
Pour mixture into greased casserole. Melt butter and stir crumbs into it.
Place on top. Cook in oven for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese and sausage strata
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add vegetables; continue cooking 5 minutes.
Drain. Cool 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, water and pumpkin. Blend.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour in two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs and melted butter. Blend well.
Add milk and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: summer fruit surprise
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and spread on the bottom of a glass dish.
With a mixer, blend the cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add the Cool Whip and mix, then the lemon juice and mix. With a spatula, fold in the fruit.
Place the mixture on top of the graham cracker crust and garnish with graham cracker crumbs. Chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: baked haddock
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan (or size suitable for amount of fish).
Preheat oven to 425°.
Dip haddock in milk and drain on paper towels.
Place fish in buttered pan; salt and pepper top of fish.
Cover fish with small pieces of bread; dot generously with small pieces of butter.
Bake for about 20 minutes.
Turn oven down to 375° after placing in oven.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Heat together Cheez Whiz, chicken soup and Pet milk to make a hot sauce.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large slow cooker, combine the first nine ingredients. Cover and cook on high for 7 hours or until the vegetables are tender.
Add milk and parsley, mix well.
Cover and cook 30-60 minutes longer or until heated through.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Brown meat; add onions, mushrooms and spices.
Place frozen spinach on top.
Cover and let steam until mixable.
Add rice, soup and sour cream.
Mix and then pour into casserole.
Spread cheese over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch creme pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water and milk.
Add butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir half in egg yolks and blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in vanilla.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly; add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with water.
Raisins may be added, if desired.
Place in greased and floured cake pans. Put in oven at 325° and gradually increase the temperature to 350° for a total of 45 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Beat margarine in large bowl until fluffy.
Beat in brown sugar, yogurt, whole egg, egg whites and 3 teaspoons lemon juice.
Set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Add flour mixture to margarine mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix in poppy seed and lemon peel.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: sea island salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes. Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, celery seed and onion salt.
Stir into macaroni.
Add remaining ingredients; toss and chill thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream margarine or butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream.
Add eggs; mix well.
Form dough into a roll, 12 inches long.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill in refrigerator until firm.
Cut into slices 1/4-inch thick.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in oven at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: swedish fruit salad
directions: Cook eggs, lemon juice and sugar over hot water until thick. Add butter, set aside and cool.
Beat heavy cream and fold into cooled egg mixture.
Add fruit and marshmallows.
Let stand overnight.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Mix broccoli, 2 cups of cheese and onion in a large pan.
Beat eggs, milk, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into a pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Top with remaining cheese and melt, 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Remove mesh from the turkey.
Lay turkey out as flat as possible on a cutting board, placing the skin side down.
Combine the garlic, rosemary, pepper and salt in the work bowl of the food processor with the steel blade in place, or in blender.
Turn motor on.
Add the oil, processing until coarsely chopped.
Spread half the garlic mixture over the inside of the turkey.
Re-roll the turkey.
Tie firmly with string every 2 inches to return the meat to its original log shape.
Spread evenly with the remaining garlic mixture.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Roast at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until a meat thermometer inserted in the center registers 170°.
A long log shape takes less time than a more compact roast.

title: sunday fried chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and oil.
Place about 1 cup flour mixture in a paper or plastic bag.
Shake a few chicken pieces in the bag at a time, coating well.
Heat 1/4 inches of oil in a large skillet on medium-high until brown on all sides.
Place in large shallow baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. Store unused mixture in an airtight container.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: popcorn crunch
directions: Blend butter and honey.
Heat until well blended.
Pour over popcorn/nut mixture.
Spread over cookie sheet in thin layer. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until crisp.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put soup in pan and heat.
Remove from heat and add meat, celery and mayonnaise.
Mix until well blended. Spoon into lightly greased casserole.
Mix stuffing mix as directed on package.
Spoon over mixture in casserole.
Bake 30 minutes until well done and bubbles up.

title: cupid's kiss(frozen drink)
directions: Blend all together to desired consistency.
Enjoy!!

title: pierogi
directions: Combine flour, eggs, sour cream and salt and knead until the dough is soft, pliable and very elastic, 30 to 45 minutes of hand kneading.

title: bavarian apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add apples and nuts.
Spread batter into an ungreased sheet cake pan (approximately 11 x 14-inch).
Bake 35 minutes or until center springs back when touched lightly.
Allow to cool slightly and serve in squares with a dusting of powdered sugar on each serving.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Brown ground beef in Dutch oven with onions and peppers.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Drain and add other ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cabbage is tender. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pumpkin cheese ball or dip
directions: Mix together well.
Roll into a ball and sprinkle with pecans or paprika.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: grilled vegetables over pasta
directions: Wash and prepare all vegetables (except tomatoes); toss with pepper.
Wash and chop tomatoes.
Toss the tomatoes with remaining herbs and spices.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Drain, flake and remove bones in salmon.
Reserve liquid in a bowl.
In another bowl, combine salmon, celery, green pepper, onion, croutons, cheese and pickle relish.
Set aside.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut beef into strips (2 x 1 x 1/4-inch). Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add beef; cook, turning frequently until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes for round steak, 5 to 8 minutes for sirloin.
Add green pepper strips during last 5 minutes of simmering.

title: chili with beans(prize winning recipe)
directions: Heat the chili, salsa, salt and pepper and simmer for at least 15 minutes.
Boil franks.
Serve franks on buns with onion (optional) and Cheddar cheese with chili.

title: apricot-date-prune pie
directions: Put apricots, dates, prunes, water and salt in saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Cover and simmer until fruit is tender and water is absorbed, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in juice and vanilla. Chill.
Roll out half of pastry and line pie plate. Fill with fruit mixture.
Roll out remaining pastry and cut into 3/4-inch strips. Arrange lattice fashion on pie.
Brush pastry with milk or egg.
Bake on bottom rack in preheated 425° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool. Serve slightly warm or cool topped with whipped cream, if desired.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions on package.
When completely cool, cut cake into 4 pieces, 2 small squares for bottom of punch bowl and 2 large squares for upper part of punch bowl.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and milk and beat hard. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and boiling water; beat hard.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot tortilla pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green chilies.
Drain. Mix together for sauce can of enchilada sauce and tomato sauce.

title: crab salad
directions: Remove the crusts from the bread.
Butter each slice and cut into small cubes.
Chop the onion and the eggs.
Add them to the bread cubes and refrigerate overnight.
Add crab, shrimp and diced celery.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. If you use less bread, cut down the amount of mayonnaise.

title: pecan pies
directions: Makes 2 pies.
Mix ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in melted butter. Roll in crumbs mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all dry ingredients into one gallon of boiling water, dissolve, serve and enjoy.

title: texas cowboy biscuits
directions: Mix yeast with milk.
Add sugar, oil, baking powder and salt. Add flour and mix.
Flour hands and form biscuits.
Put close together in baking pan and let them rise for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all together, except cherries.
Add 1 cup maraschino cherries, cut in half.
Add 1 cup walnuts (optional).
Put in Bundt pan and bake at 350° for approximately 55 minutes.

title: chicken in the grass
directions: Place chicken in Pyrex baking dish.
Put layer of broccoli over top.
Pour over can of cream of mushroom, then layer of broccoli again, then other can of soup.
Sprinkle Parmesan or Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: keepsake brownies
directions: Melt chocolate squares with butter.
Remove and add sugar, eggs, vanilla, water, flour and salt.
Stir in walnuts.
Put in greased and floured 11 x 7-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green tomatoes pepper relish
directions: Chunk tomatoes and cover with salt.
Let sit while preparing remaining ingredients. Drain tomatoes and all remaining ingredients. Cook until tomatoes are tender.
Pack in sterilized jar and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix and cook in moderate oven.

title: cauliflower with almonds
directions: Trim leaves from cauliflower, leaving 1-inch of stem for support.
Place in Dutch oven.
Add hot water that covers stem, but does not touch head.
Cover and steam until tender, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: party beans
directions: Brown and drain the ground meat.
Saute onions; fry bacon to a crisp and crumble bacon.
Combine with all the ingredients except bacon.
Put in dish.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Put the bacon on top the last 5 or 10 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough onto a pizza pan.
Bake according to directions on package; cool.
Make filling by combining cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Mix well and spread onto cooled cookie dough.
Drain fruits and place on top of filling, putting pineapple on outside, strawberries in the middle and kiwi in the center.
I enjoy these fruits, however any can be used.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in pot and heat thoroughly.

title: black bean and bulgur chili
directions: Bean Preparation:
One pound of dried beans will make about 6 cups, cooked and drained.
After picking out stones, rinse. Transfer to big pot.
Cover with 3 quarts of water.
Bring to boil for several minutes and then soak.
Drain, rinse and cover with water plus 1/2-inch for cooking process.
Bring to simmer; cover pot and cook for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: cheese danish(serves 24)
directions: Place 2 packages crescent roll mix on bottom of large cookie sheet.
Combine cream cheese, egg, sugar and flavoring in large bowl and cream together.
Spread mixture over rolls and top with other 2 packages of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: microwave walnut penuche
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
Grease lightly.
Let foil extend above 2 sides.

title: jello salad
directions: Prepare jello with hot water; put into refrigerator until consistency of thick syrup.
Stir in remaining ingredients; thicken in a fairly large bowl or jello mold.

title: easy vegetable quiche
directions: Bake shells at 400° for 6 minutes.
Add milk, soup and eggs; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and distribute evenly over 2 shells.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: 300 dollar chocolate cake
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add this mixture to 2 cups of plain flour and 2 cups of sugar. Then add the buttermilk, soda, salt and eggs. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise and garlic salt together.
Combine potatoes, onions and Bac*Os.
Mix cheese sauce and potatoes mixture; reserve some sauce for top.
Place in large casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: arroz con leche(rice with milk)
directions: Bring water to a boil with cinnamon sticks.
Add rice.
When done, add the milks and sugar (to taste). Stir well.
Add vanilla and raisins. Cook to boiling point and remove from heat.
Good luck.

title: crackers with melted cheese
directions: Put the cheese on a plate; arrange the crackers on plate.
Put them in microwave for 20 seconds.
If the cheese is not melted, microwave 10 seconds more.

title: pecans delight
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat and mix well.
Fold in nuts and crumbs.
Mix carefully and pour into a well-greased 9-inch pie pan (I use Pam). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 2 hours.
Top with whipped cream and pecans.
Makes at least 6 servings.
Very good; very easy.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Then stir in apples.
Drop by large tablespoon into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with apple butter on the side.

title: almond tea cookies(preparation time: 15 minutes. bake time: 10 to 12 minutes.)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cream butter flavor Crisco, milk and almond extract in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended. Beat in granulated sugar. Combine flour, almonds and salt. Mix into creamed mixture. Shape dough into balls using 1 level measuring tablespoon for each. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. (Cookies will not brown. Do not overbake.)
