Remove to cooling rack. Roll slightly warm cookie in confectioners sugar. Roll in confectioners sugar again when cookies are cool. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: green beans with potatoes casserole
directions: Drain beans and potatoes.
Stir ingredients together. (Reserve 1/4 can onion rings and sprinkle on top.)
Pour into casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: savory crescent turkey squares(makes four servings)
directions: Blend cheese, oleo and milk until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Separate crescent rolls into four rectangles.
Pinch perforations together to seal.
Divide mixture evenly.
Place on the four squares.
Pull four corners together and seal all edges to prevent leakage.
Brush tops with melted oleo and dip into crouton crumbs.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; stir in strawberries, banana and pineapple.
Pour 1/2 mix in mold; let congeal until firm. Spread with sour cream.
Add remainder of mixture and congeal. Serves 6 to 8.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak vegetables overnight in salt water (1/2 cup to 2 quarts water); drain.
Heat to boiling the remaining ingredients.
Add vegetables; return to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pack in sterile jars.
Process in boiling water bath.
Increase vinegar spice mix as needed for amount of vegetables.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients, putting bacon and eggs on last.
Spoon Miracle Whip and spread over ingredients, sealing to edge of pan (if possible).
Sprinkle sugar on top of Miracle Whip and then sprinkle on cheese.
Keeps well if you need to make it the night before.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix ingredients well and put in greased pan.
Top with grated nippy cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: onion soup
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions until golden.
In a medium saucepan combine sauteed onions and beef broth.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat; then simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
In a broiler, toast French bread on both sides.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and grated Parmesan cheese.
Broil just until cheeses are bubbly, approximately 1 minute.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Mix all other ingredients.
Put 1/2 ground beef in bottom of 8-inch square baking dish.
Put 1/2 above mixture over it.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese. Repeat with second layer.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cornbread mixture is done.

title: brown rice
directions: Put rice in casserole dish, add french onion undrained, beef consomme undrained.
Cut butter into small slices.
Drain juices off of mushrooms.
Cook on 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add mincemeat to mix.
Blend in eggs; add flour mixture, alternating with soup.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 80 minutes.
Can be covered with white frosting or hard sauce.

title: filled pepper soup
directions: Combine all after browning hamburg in large pot.
Simmer at least 1 hour, stirring often.

title: cheese dip
directions: You will need 3 Old English jars.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar and jello.
Boil for 2 minutes. Cool.
When cool add cottage cheese and topping.
Mix well.
Pour into mold or bowl and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: shay's corn and bean casserole
directions: Combine the corn, bread, onions and 1/2 of the shredded cheese with mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered casserole dish and top with remaining cheese and the bread squares.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until bread cubes are lightly browned.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in container with a tight lid.
Use 2 1/2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in the order given in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: swedish excellent salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
In saucepan, bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar and oil.
Slightly cool.
Pour over other ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook angel hair.
Brown hamburg and pepperoni.
Add seasonings, if desired.
In baking dish, put in angel hair.
Add spaghetti sauce, cottage cheese, hamburg and pepperoni.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat in oil or oleo.
Add garlic, salt and pepper, sugar, spaghetti sauce and Tabasco.
Mix together the sour cream, cream cheese, onions and chilies.
In 2 (2-quart) casseroles, layer the noodles, cream cheese mixture, meat and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked round steak
directions: Cut round steak in slices.
Trim fat.
Pound well on both sides.
Dip in beaten egg and seasoned bread crumbs and brown. Pour one-half cup water in roaster or whatever.
Put round steak brown on top and bake 1/2 hour at 350° with cover, then heat gravy and mushrooms and pour over round steak and continue baking for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Rinse frozen peas.
Mix all ingredients except lettuce and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate an hour or so.
Before serving, mix in lettuce and bacon.
Makes a lot.

title: bacon cheese potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes; place in a saucepan and cover with water. Cook until tender but firm; drain and cube.
In a bowl, mix potatoes with the onion, cheese and mayonnaise.
Transfer to an ungreased 13x9x2 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with bacon and olives.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
If desired, sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Yield: 8-10 servings.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Beat together butter, oil, sugar and powdered sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat.
Add flour, soda and cream of tartar and beat.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto cookie sheet (do not grease).
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown around the edges.
These cookies will be very tender if you don't overbake.

title: garlic cheese roll
directions: You will need wax paper.

title: garlan's original strawberry cake
directions: Follow directions on box of cake mix; bake two 9-inch round layers.
When completely cool, split layers with thread, making 4 layers.
Wash strawberries; save 7 or 8 pretty berries for top. Slice berries, add sugar, mix and set aside.
Bake cake, cool and split layers.
Add Cool Whip to berry mixture and blend well. Spread between layers and on top.
Garnish top with remaining berries.

title: pierogi
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add onion, cheese, butter, salt and pepper to mashed potatoes and mix well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder into a bowl.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Combine well and turn out onto floured board and knead for 10 minutes. Roll dough to form circle 1/4-inch thick.
Cut circle of dough with a 5-inch cutter.
Fill circles with tablespoon of potato filling.
Fold dough in half.
Seal edges by moistening with water and pressing with fork 1/4-inch at edge.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.
Serves 25.

title: corn burger pie
directions: Combine meat and onion in large skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain well.
Prepare spaghetti sauce mix according to package instructions.
Add sauce and green beans to meat mixture. Bring to boil, stirring well.
Remove from heat and pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Prepare cornbread mix and pour over meat.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, apple pie spice and salt together in bowl.
Add milk.
Batter will be like thin pancake batter.
Melt butter in loaf pan.
Pour 3/4 batter into pan, then peaches (undrained) on top of batter.
Pour rest of batter on top of peaches.
Bake at 325° until done.
Serve warm.

title: roast coon
directions: Mix all the
ingredients
and
stuff
coon and place in roasting pan.
Add water and cook slowly at 350° until tender.

title: pecan fudge pie
directions: In pan, over low heat, melt chocolate and butter.
Stir in milk, hot water and eggs; mix well.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining
ingredients.
Bake
to
45 minutes at 350°. Cool. Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill one hour.
Roll on floured board to 1/2-inch.
Cut and bake at 325° about 10 minutes.

title: pimiento-squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Add soup, sour cream, pimiento and pepper.
Melt butter; blend with dry stuffing mix.
Grease 8 1/2 x 12 1/2-inch dish or three 8-inch pans; spread a layer of dressing mix in pan.
Pour in squash mixture; cover with remaining dressing mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: great potatoes
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top, then sprinkle corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until lightly browned.

title: fruit bars
directions: Place water in a saucepan.
Sprinkle gelatin over water. Allow gelatin to soften for 5 minutes.
Stir over low heat to dissolve gelatin.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Place mixture into a blender, 1/3 at a time.
Blend until mixture has a coarse texture, but contains not large chunks.
Add blended ingredients to gelatin in saucepan; stir well.
Line bottom and sides of an 8-inch square pan with wax paper.
Spray wax paper with a nonstick spray.
Spread mixture in pan.
Cool completely in refrigerator until firm, about 2 to 3 hours.
Cut into 24 bars. Store bars between layers of wax paper.
Yields 24 bars.

title: marti's chicken and rice soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water (or broth), rice with contents of seasoning packet and soup mix. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Stir in celery, carrot and onion. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Stir in chicken soup and chicken. Cover and cook 8 minutes or until rice and vegetables are tender. Makes 5 servings.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and cool completely under cool, running water.
Add dressing, basil and cheese to taste.
Add frozen peas, thawed in microwave approximately 2 minutes or less.
Stir and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Cook chicken under broiler or on the grill; don't overcook. Brush a thin layer of barbecue sauce over each side.
Continue to cook until slightly brown.
Put enough cheese to cover each piece of chicken, cook until melted.
Put chicken on plate and top with chopped tomatoes, onions and mushrooms.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add onions, peppers, celery and tomatoes, then add rice. Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Pour in large baking dish and bake for about 45 minutes at 350°, stirring occasionally.

title: foolproof whip cream icing
directions: Cook flour and milk, stirring until it makes a heavy white sauce.
Remove from fire, cool.
(May place in refrigerator until thickens.)
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add white sauce and beat at high speed until it resembles whipped cream.
Add vanilla and blend.
Covers an 8-inch cake.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in greased dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, salad dressing, lemon juice and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Place
this
mixture
in
a wide-mouth glass or earthen crock. Cover
with cheesecloth to allow wild yeast of the air to settle on it for 24 hours.
Cover and let it ferment for 2 weeks.
Keep permanently in the covered jar.

title: hungarian scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
When cool, clean and slice in rings.
Slice hard-boiled eggs in rings.
Melt butter in small pan.
In casserole, layer potatoes, eggs, salt and pepper and small amount of butter.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used.
Top with sour cream.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or lightly browned.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Crush crackers and add to melted margarine.
Pat into 9 inch pie plate, lining sides and bottom and sides, saving 1/4 cup for top.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 7 - 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: cracker candy
directions: In medium bowl, mix peanut butter and vanilla.
In medium saucepan, mix sugar and cream together.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over peanut butter and vanilla mixture and beat for 2 minutes with electric mixer or until it thickens.
Add crushed crackers and mix with a spoon.
Press in a buttered pan.
It will be very thick and will set up fast.
May be cut right away.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips (about 2 inches long).
Saute mushrooms in oil.
Remove.
Using same oil, saute onion and remove.
Brown meat on both sides.
Blend flour in oil.
Add bouillon, stirring constantly.
Add paste and seasonings.
Combine all ingredients in double boiler.
Cook 20 minutes.
Blend in yogurt 5 minutes before serving.

title: cream cheese braids
directions: Combine scalded sour cream, sugar, butter and salt.
Mix well; let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in sour cream mixture, then eggs.
Gradually stir in flour (dough will be stiff).
Cover tightly and chill overnight.

title: lynn's quick mex dip
directions: Mix together.
Good when warmed in microwave.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookies will be soft.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute before removing.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions. Drain fat. Place in greased casserole dish and cover with cheese and seasoning. Place potatoes over meat and cheese.
Mix milk with mushroom soup and pour over top. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stir-fried deer
directions: Combine sherry, soy sauce, cornstarch, salt and garlic. Marinate meat in mixture for 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat oil in wok or deep heavy skillet.
Stir-fry deer, green pepper and onion until meat is done (about 6 minutes).
Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pumpkin, vanilla, lemon peel and juice. Sift flour with baking powder, salt and spices.
Blend into butter mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: diane's soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 4 items.
Add sour milk and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add a little more flour if needed.
Roll on floured counter to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes (do not overbake).
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: brownies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and alternate mixing with milk to egg mixture. Bake in square, greased pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: quick and tender steak
directions: Slice chopped steak into 1-inch slices.
Roll in salt, pepper and flour.
Brown in oil (do not cook through).
Drain oil.
Add soup and 2 cans water.
Cover pan with tight lid.
Reduce heat; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Will make its own gravy.
Very good served over rice.

title: fettuccine salad
directions: In large pot, bring 1 gallon water to a vigorous boil.
Add oil, liquid from corn and salt.
Break fettuccine and drop into boiling liquid.
Cook until pasta is done (al dente).
Pour into colander.
Rinse completely with cool water.
Combine crushed bouillon cubes, corn, Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, green onions and seasonings.
Microwave briefly, just until warm.
Stir to blend.
Put cold pasta in large bowl.
Pour sauce over pasta.
Mix well.
Serve chilled.
Makes 6 to 8 large servings.

title: fresh peach pound cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Cool completely on rack.

title: chocolate pie(quick, easy and good)
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan over medium heat, stirring until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes. Stir twice while cooling.
Pour into shell.
Cool 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: mama's chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Cool, then remove from bone. Set aside. Cook onions, milk and soup until tender. Cut chicken in bite size. Put in large baking dish. Pour soup mixture over chicken. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix stuffing according to box. Spoon over chicken. Bake until heated well. Serve hot.

title: quick apple bread
directions: Beat egg and oil in a large bowl.
Add apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Gradually stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Mix other ingredients as listed and mix thoroughly.
(Cheese must be grated.)

title: broccoli with cream cheese sauce
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Make sauce with cheese, milk, juice and garlic salt.
Place broccoli in serving bowl and pour sauce over.
Garnish with pieces of pimento or red pepper.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat eggs well; mix with sugar and flour.
Add the pineapple.
Put in a greased baking dish. Crumble bread on top; slice the stick of butter on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Delicious served as a side dish with baked ham.

title: lentil soup
directions: Cook lentils according to package directions.
Cook other vegetables until tender.
Combine all ingredients in large pot. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy grape jelly
directions: Wash grapes.
Strain with Foley mill.
Boil ingredients 20 minutes; strain and immediately pour into jars.

title: flan(practically fat-free)
directions: Caramelize 3/4 cup sugar in heavy skillet over medium heat until a rich brown color. Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch oval baking dish, rotating to cover the sides evenly (warm dish first). Cool. In a large bowl, beat egg substitute. Gradually add remaining sugar. In a large saucepan on medium heat, stir milk and cinnamon stick. When milk bubbles, remove stick, then slowly add milk mixture to egg mixture, stirring constantly. Stir in vanilla. Place all combined ingredients into the oval baking dish. Place in a larger baking dish and add water to 1-inch height in the outer pan. Bake in a preheated 325° oven, uncovered, about 90 minutes. Because of all the fat-free ingredients, it takes longer to set up. Cool on wire rack and refrigerate up to 6 hours before unmolding. Loosen edges of flan with a spatula and invert. Rectangle cooking pans will do; ovals are prettier. Serves 8.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and 1 cup of water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick and clear.
Stir constantly; cool slightly.
Stir in gelatin and food coloring until gelatin dissolves.
Arrange strawberries in a pie shell. Pour glaze over the top.
Garnish with cream and additional strawberries.

title: puppy chow or white trash
directions: Mix peanut butter, melted chocolate chips and margarine.
Pour over Rice Chex, coating as evenly as possible.
Dump coated cereal into bag of powdered sugar and shake well.
Seal in container; keeps well.

title: sauerkraut meatballs
directions: Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Do not brown.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes more or less as desired. Mexican cornbread is good with this.

title: italian fish soup
directions: In a soup kettle, saute garlic and onions in olive oil until they are soft and translucent.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, carrot, celery and eggplant.
(If you use zucchini, add it with the green pepper.) Mix well.
Add oregano, black pepper and basil.
Cover and cook over low heat, 5 to 8 minutes.
Add green pepper, stock, puree, cooked beans and wine.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and remaining salt.
Keep at lowest heat until 10 minutes before you plan to serve.
Then, heat the soup to a boil.
Add pasta, and boil gently until pasta is tender.
Serve immediately, topped with parsley and Parmesan.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: healthy egg salad
directions: Combine and chill.
Can be used as sandwiches, egg filler, stuffed tomatoes or green peppers.
Rolled up in thin canned biscuit dough baked at 325° for 4 to 5 minutes makes excellent egg puffs.
Serve hot.

title: dutch split pea soup
directions: Bring peas, ham hocks and water to a boil.
Skim froth off; simmer 1 hour partially covered.
Add 1/2 slab bacon (no rind) and simmer 1 hour.
In large skillet, saute 2 1/2 to 3 cups leeks in 2 tablespoons butter for 8 minutes. Add 1/2 teaspoon minced garlic and saute 2 minutes.
Add to the kettle with the celery and simmer 1 hour.
Remove ham hocks and cut up the meat.
Return to soup. Add 3/4 pound Polish sausage (halved lengthwise and cut into 1/4 inch slices).
Simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Let soup stand overnight, uncovered.
Reheat and add 1/2 cup dry white wine and 1/2 cup light cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with minced parsley.

title: hearty oats 'n wheat loaves(winning recipe; a wholesome bread for toast, sandwich or dinner)
directions: Generously grease two 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups bread flour, oats, salt and yeast.
Blend well.
In medium saucepan, heat water, corn syrup and margarine until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid and eggs to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in whole wheat flour and rye flour to form a soft dough.
On floured surface, knead in up to 1 cup bread flour until dough is smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel.
Let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until light and doubled in size, about 1 hour.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in large salad bowl in order listed. Let marinate at least 12 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter and beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add bananas.
Sift flour with baking powder and soda.
Stir flour into egg mixture and add vanilla.
Fold in sour cream and add nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add into mixture, then pour in pie crusts and bake.
When cool, add Cool Whip if desired.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place about 30 minutes or until soft and puffed.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tar heel pie
directions: Pour warm melted oleo over chocolate chips and let stand. Measure the rest of the ingredients.
Stir melted chocolate and oleo with rest of the ingredients.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. After pie cools, top with Cool Whip.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Grease a pan good.
Place rice on bottom.
Place cut up chicken on top of rice.
Blend all other ingredients together. Pour liquid (soup and hot water) over chicken; sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours (1 hour covered and 1 hour uncovered).
Use in a roaster.
Enjoy!

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer whole crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 pudding mixture. Add another layer of pudding and crackers, ending with crackers. Spread chocolate icing on top.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl, except flour; mix well. Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Dough will be softer than regular dough.
Turn out on floured surface, knead lightly a few times.
Roll to 1/4 inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Makes 17 biscuits.
Use only 1/4 cup sugar if potatoes are naturally sweet and juicy.

title: amaretto fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Beat in preserves and Amaretto until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Enjoy with fruit of your choice.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients together and store in airtight container. Add 1 to 2 teaspoons to cup of hot water. Very good!

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon into hot deep fat.
Cook until golden brown and center is done.
Can be mixed ahead of time, but do not stir any more.
Yield:
Approximately 15.

title: yummy crackers
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Mix together oil and all other ingredients, except crackers.
Put crackers in large bowl, mix other ingredients in small cup or dish, then pour over crackers. Thoroughly mix until every cracker is coated.
(It looks greasy, but they aren't).
Let stand 1 to 2 hours and mix often.
They are finished when the crackers look dry.

title: easy casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
In a pan, saute the onion, garlic and chili flakes in oil.
Saute until onion is transparent, then add to soup mixture.
Spread mixture into a casserole dish.

title: goulash soup
directions: If you like a zip to your soup, 1/2 teaspoon of hot paprika can be combined with regular paprika for 1 tablespoon.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel and core apples. Grind pears and oranges and lemon (with skins). Add sugar and cook 1 to 2 hours or until thick. Add pineapple and boil briskly for 45 minutes. Put in jars and cover firmly. After 1 hour, seal tightly.

title: light and fluffy salad
directions: You will need 1 large rectangle dish.

title: louisiana shrimp and corn gumbo
directions: In a large pan over medium heat, make a dark roux with olive oil and flour, stirring constantly.
When brown, add onions, green pepper, green onions and parsley.
Saute on low for 10 minutes. Add salt, pepper, cayenne, Cajun seasoning, hot sauce, Worcestershire and basil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add corn, tomatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add shrimp during last 15 to 20 minutes of cooking time.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: fried yellow squash
directions: Slice squash in 1/4 inch slices.
Dip into egg wash and into cornmeal.
Place into hot oil and fry until brown.

title: irish creme
directions: Mix all together. Lasts refrigerated 6 weeks.

title: heavenly delights
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add 2/3 cup sugar and flavorings, beating until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour; beat well.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove immediately from cookie sheets and roll in powdered sugar. Cool and roll again in powdered sugar.
Yields about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: overnight fiesta salad
directions: Layer first 9 ingredients in order listed in a large salad bowl. Cover tightly.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Top with corn chips. Toss gently before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Whip the first 4 ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Pour into two 8-inch graham cracker crusts.
Chill 1 hour.
May garnish with lemon slices.
Very light dessert after heavy meal.

title: potato puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop a teaspoon of mixture in deep fat at medium heat.
Fry like doughnuts.
Drain.
Serve with syrup, honey, jelly or butter.

title: poppers
directions: Slice open one side of pepper.
Clean out seeds, depending on taste.
Fill with cheese.
Mix milk, egg, flour and salt.
Beat into batter.
Heat oil.
Dip into batter.
Deep fry.
Drain on paper towel.

title: beer-cheese soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots until soft.
Put in soup pot. Add chicken broth.
Heat until very warm.
Add Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Mix cheese with flour and add to soup.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add beer.
Serve with garlic croutons.
Sausage can be added for a complete meal.

title: puff dessert pie
directions: Boil 1 cup water and 1 stick of oleo.
Add flour.
Beat 4 eggs one at a time into flour mixture.
Spread in an oblong pan.
Mix can of pumpkin, 2 cans of milk, 2 eggs, brown sugar and pumpkin spices.
Pour on top of the spread mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 375° and cook for 45 minutes more.
Check with knife and if clean, it's done.
This has a nice brown crust on top.

title: ranch style lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils, drain and combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil and reduce heat. Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until lentils are tender.
May be garnished with thin slices of wieners or smoked sausage.
Ummm good!!!!

title: canadian cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Mix dry ingredients and add to other.
Chill. Roll in balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add oil, sugar, zucchini, then add flour, baking powder, soda, salt, vanilla, cinnamon and nuts. Grease and flour pans. Bake in 9 x 13 pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
You may bake in 2 loaf pans about 1 hour at 350° or five 4-inch by 8-inch loaf pans for 40 minutes or Bundt pan for 40 minutes.

title: old line oyster pie
directions: Place bottom crust in pie pan.
Put in well drained potatoes. Remove oysters from containers with slotted spoon and put over potatoes.
Set aside oyster liquor to make a sauce.
Place egg slices over oysters.
Dot butter over top and sprinkle with celery salt and lemon pepper seasoning.
Place top crust on pie.
Cut slits in top.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Lower to 375° until crust is lightly brown, about 30 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Drain.

title: kay's crab cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and add crackers and crab meat. Mix lightly not to separate lumps.
Makes about 6 crab cakes.

title: rolls
directions: Mix yeast and hot water.
Scald milk.
Add sugar, shortening and salt to milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add flour and beat well.
Add egg and yeast water.
Add 1 1/2 cups more flour.
Mix well.
Put in greased bowl.
Turn dough to grease the top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double.
Place on floured board and knead.
Pinch off rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Drain the juice from the tomatoes.
Put in heavy saucepan and mash with potato masher.
Chop the cheese in the tomatoes and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching.
When cheese is melted, pour in the chili and heat thoroughly.
(The chili may be subbed with 1 pound pork sausage, browned and drained.)
The dip may be prepared in a crock-pot and left on low as being served.
Serve warm with chips.

title: chocolate chunk banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir eggs, bananas, oil and milk until well blended.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir until just moistened.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: glorified gingerbread cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, shortening, ginger and cinnamon as for a pie crust (crumbly).
Remove 1/2 cup of this and set aside.
Into the rest, add egg, molasses, milk, soda and salt.
Blend well, pour into a greased 7 x 12-inch greased cake pan.
Crumble the remaining crumbs over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, cake test with toothpick.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Combine with rest of ingredients. Form balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet, but do not crowd.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Can be mixed and frozen until ready to bake.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours before slicing.

title: potato skins
directions: Heat bacon fat in saucepan.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms; season well.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes over medium heat. Mix well and continue cooking another 8 minutes over low heat.

title: ham and swiss hero sandwiches
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and mustard; blend well.
Spread cut surfaces of bread halves with cream cheese mixture.
Place bottom half of bread on large ungreased cookie sheet.
Layer with ham, lettuce, tomato, cheese and onion.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.
To serve, cut into slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fire and ice pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients; let set 2 hours.
Stir occasionally. Put in pint jar kept in refrigerator.
Makes about 3 pints.
Longer they set, the better they get.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut shortening into flour mixture; add milk.
Form into balls; bake in round pan at 350° until golden brown and tests done with a toothpick.

title: pizza ritz
directions: Melt cheese.
Stir in sausage, soy sauce and salt.
Spoon onto bread.
Bake at 375° until bubbly and brown around the edges.
Use hot sausage if you dare.

title: deep-dish pizza
directions: Brown together meats, onions and peppers.
Drain well.
Stir in tomatoes, pizza sauce and oregano to taste.
Simmer 15 minutes. Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pizza dough.
With greased fingers, press into bottom and up sides of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese slices, meat sauce, then cheese slices and meat sauce again; cover with shredded cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: healthy chili
directions: Spray a large stockpot with nonstick cooking spray and heat over medium-high heat until hot. Add half of the meat and cook until browned. Remove from heat and drain. Repeat with remaining meat.

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in milk and cook over medium-low heat until slightly thickened.
Combine a little of hot mixture with beaten egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture and cook until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Top cooled filling with meringue made by beating egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff enough to hold in peaks.
Brown in hot oven at 425° for about 5 minutes.

title: zesty grilled chicken lo-fat!
directions: Place chicken breasts in a shallow glass dish (or a Ziploc bag works well, too).
Prepare marinade with remaining ingredients. Pour marinade over chicken and refrigerate a minimum of 4 hours. May be refrigerated up to 24 hours.
Grill quickly over hot coals, basting frequently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: date-nut bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Beat eggs until light.
Gradually add sugar, beating to smooth and fluffy.
At low speed beat in flour mixture until well combined, then stir in dates and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Cool slightly.
Cut into bars while still warm.
Let cool completely in pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: coquilles st. jacques
directions: Toss bread crumbs with 1 tablespoon of margarine; set aside. Stir together the next 4 ingredients; set aside.
In skillet, cook scallops in 2 tablespoons of margarine until opaque.
Drain well. Cook mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons margarine for 3 minutes. Add to cheese mixture with scallops.
Spoon into 6 individual baking dishes or shells or casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Broil 6 inches from heat source until browned, at least 4 minutes for shells or individual dishes, longer for casserole. Serves 6.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple. Add marshmallows and coconut. Stir in sour cream.
Sprinkle some coconut over top of salad.

title: self-rising flour
directions: Put into a container with a tight lid and store in refrigerator.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Add nuts, chocolate chips or fruit, if you wish.
(I sometimes divide the dough and put nuts in part and chocolate chips in part).
Divide dough into 3 or 4 rolls and chill in the refrigerator.
Slice and bake at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Pat into small patties and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together well.
Bake in an 8 or 9-inch greased and floured pan at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the tortillas, and spread mixture on individual tortillas. Roll up jelly roll style, wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap and refrigerate, preferably overnight, until well chilled.
Slice and serve as pinwheels.

title: carrot cake
directions: Assemble and mix ingredients in order listed.
Put in 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Frost with creamy white icing (ready made).

title: quick cherry cream parfait
directions: In mixer bowl, combine milk, sour cream and almond extract. Add pudding mix and beat with rotary or electric beater until creamy and well blended, about 2 minutes.
Fill parfait glasses with alternate layers of pudding, cherry pie filling and almonds. Chill.
Garnish with additional almonds.
Makes 6 parfaits.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over chicken in large baking dish. Bake at 500° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 20 minutes.

title: sugar buns
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and corn syrup in a saucepan. Bring to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the pecans. Divide mixture evenly among 12 muffin pan wells.
Place 2 rolls in each cup well.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately. Yields one dozen buns.
